1
00:00:00,648 --> 00:00:02,587
(The smell of spring...)

2
00:00:02,588 --> 00:00:05,018
(is everywhere on this April day.)

3
00:00:06,018 --> 00:00:07,587
(Where are we at?)

4
00:00:07,588 --> 00:00:11,127
This train will soon arrive at Naju Station.

5
00:00:11,128 --> 00:00:12,428
(We're at Naju Station.)

6
00:00:12,898 --> 00:00:15,357
I'm 90 percent back to normal.

7
00:00:15,358 --> 00:00:16,628
Are you two twinning?

8
00:00:16,868 --> 00:00:17,868
You're dressed alike...

9
00:00:17,869 --> 00:00:19,237
- and you're dressed alike.
- Yes.

10
00:00:19,238 --> 00:00:20,437
- How come?
- How come?

11
00:00:20,438 --> 00:00:22,137
Why are we dressed like this?

12
00:00:22,138 --> 00:00:23,638
- What's going on?
- How do you feel?

13
00:00:23,738 --> 00:00:25,407
- Are you better?
- I feel much better.

14
00:00:25,408 --> 00:00:26,408
Do you?

15
00:00:26,409 --> 00:00:28,378
Why do you pretend to care all of a sudden?

16
00:00:29,078 --> 00:00:31,708
You pretend to care now that the cameras are rolling.

17
00:00:31,848 --> 00:00:33,517
You're my best buddies.

18
00:00:33,518 --> 00:00:35,648
- You guys all called.
- Really?

19
00:00:35,718 --> 00:00:37,147
- You called...
- Everyone?

20
00:00:37,148 --> 00:00:38,617
If we have to play a game,

21
00:00:38,618 --> 00:00:40,517
will you blame your back and back out?

22
00:00:40,518 --> 00:00:42,257
- You...
- Just go home.

23
00:00:42,258 --> 00:00:44,028
We can always call Jae Jun.

24
00:00:44,428 --> 00:00:46,197
- Go home.
- He can come even now.

25
00:00:46,198 --> 00:00:47,997
Jae Jun, you can rest at home.

26
00:00:47,998 --> 00:00:49,598
He can even come from the airport.

27
00:00:49,798 --> 00:00:51,468
He's waiting in Gwangju.

28
00:00:52,068 --> 00:00:53,768
That's just 30 minutes away.

29
00:00:53,868 --> 00:00:55,667
- Half an hour from here?
- Yes, in Gwangju.

30
00:00:55,668 --> 00:00:57,107
He didn't come all the way here.

31
00:00:57,108 --> 00:00:59,228
You should go straight home if you get injured again.

32
00:00:59,738 --> 00:01:01,307
This is Naju Station.

33
00:01:01,308 --> 00:01:03,777
- Hello.
- Hello.

34
00:01:03,778 --> 00:01:05,608
- Hello.
- Seon Ho's back.

35
00:01:06,348 --> 00:01:07,647
- What's that?
- Are you okay?

36
00:01:07,648 --> 00:01:08,747
I'm fine.

37
00:01:08,748 --> 00:01:09,787
I'm doing much better.

38
00:01:09,788 --> 00:01:11,118
While rehearsing for the musical,

39
00:01:11,348 --> 00:01:13,418
I sprained myself slightly.

40
00:01:13,458 --> 00:01:15,618
- Are there stunts?
- There's a lot of movement.

41
00:01:16,058 --> 00:01:17,887
- There's a lot.
- Can you bend over?

42
00:01:17,888 --> 00:01:19,057
I can now.

43
00:01:19,058 --> 00:01:20,957
- Watch out.
- He hurt his back.

44
00:01:20,958 --> 00:01:22,127
- Did you stay at home?
- At first,

45
00:01:22,128 --> 00:01:23,527
I couldn't even lean forward.

46
00:01:23,528 --> 00:01:25,467
To the fans who hoped for your return.

47
00:01:25,468 --> 00:01:27,967
Yes. Thanks so much for your concern.

48
00:01:27,968 --> 00:01:29,638
I'm doing much better now.

49
00:01:29,868 --> 00:01:31,607
I'll do my best today.

50
00:01:31,608 --> 00:01:34,078
Spin your hips to show how well you are.

51
00:01:34,508 --> 00:01:35,637
I'm scared.

52
00:01:35,638 --> 00:01:37,407
- Not too much.
- You are better.

53
00:01:37,408 --> 00:01:39,148
- Nice.
- Your back is fine.

54
00:01:39,318 --> 00:01:40,947
You should thank Jae Jun too.

55
00:01:40,948 --> 00:01:42,177
You said he's in Gwangju.

56
00:01:42,178 --> 00:01:43,518
Yes, he's nearby.

57
00:01:44,388 --> 00:01:47,157
He'll join us if anyone is injured on set.

58
00:01:47,158 --> 00:01:48,287
(Waiting 30 minutes away?)

59
00:01:48,288 --> 00:01:50,528
You can go back to Seoul.

60
00:01:50,658 --> 00:01:51,958
- I'll do my best.
- Okay.

61
00:01:52,228 --> 00:01:54,897
We can't seem to reach U-Know Yunho.

62
00:01:54,898 --> 00:01:56,227
- What's going on?
- Yunho...

63
00:01:56,228 --> 00:01:58,567
- went hiking with you guys.
- Yes, with us.

64
00:01:58,568 --> 00:02:00,537
Was he smiling even at the end?

65
00:02:00,538 --> 00:02:01,697
- Or...
- He was upbeat.

66
00:02:01,698 --> 00:02:02,737
- Was he?
- Yes.

67
00:02:02,738 --> 00:02:05,407
I'll describe the ending right as we left for home.

68
00:02:05,408 --> 00:02:07,108
Yunho started off powerfully.

69
00:02:07,938 --> 00:02:09,247
(Full of passion at the start)

70
00:02:09,248 --> 00:02:10,348
"DinDin!"

71
00:02:10,648 --> 00:02:12,878
In the end, in the car, he said, "Bye, Se Yoon."

72
00:02:13,848 --> 00:02:15,248
"Bye, Se Yoon."

73
00:02:15,378 --> 00:02:17,047
- "See you around."
- He was hoarse?

74
00:02:17,048 --> 00:02:18,247
"See you around."

75
00:02:18,248 --> 00:02:19,888
He said he'd never lost his voice.

76
00:02:20,418 --> 00:02:21,857
- He lost it here.
- TVXQ...

77
00:02:21,858 --> 00:02:22,987
does so many concerts...

78
00:02:22,988 --> 00:02:24,327
and he couldn't shout "Who are we?"

79
00:02:24,328 --> 00:02:25,527
He lost his voice?

80
00:02:25,528 --> 00:02:28,428
He did this. "2 Days..."

81
00:02:28,728 --> 00:02:29,998
(You can do it!)

82
00:02:30,368 --> 00:02:31,627
(3 seconds...)

83
00:02:31,628 --> 00:02:32,898
(and you'll get used to it!)

84
00:02:33,668 --> 00:02:35,938
(He injected everyone with passion all day long.)

85
00:02:36,408 --> 00:02:38,408
(Ah-ah. 2 Days.)

86
00:02:38,508 --> 00:02:40,577
(This is how he ended up.)

87
00:02:40,578 --> 00:02:43,378
I couldn't reach Yunho until 9pm.

88
00:02:43,908 --> 00:02:45,107
At around 9pm...

89
00:02:45,108 --> 00:02:47,148
"I just got back to reality."

90
00:02:47,748 --> 00:02:50,217
- "I'm about to go get an IV drip."
- At 9pm?

91
00:02:50,218 --> 00:02:52,117
An IV drip? Was it that bad?

92
00:02:52,118 --> 00:02:53,957
- We're at Naju Station.
- Yes.

93
00:02:53,958 --> 00:02:56,128
I'll explain today's destination.

94
00:02:56,388 --> 00:02:59,397
Spring flowers bloom along the Yeongsan River.

95
00:02:59,398 --> 00:03:03,668
(Spring flowers by Yeongsan River welcome you.)

96
00:03:04,228 --> 00:03:06,937
It's a city where history and tradition lives and breathes.

97
00:03:06,938 --> 00:03:08,137
(History and tradition is well preserved.)

98
00:03:08,138 --> 00:03:10,067
This is former Naju Station,

99
00:03:10,068 --> 00:03:12,677
a well-preserved example of a previously working station.

100
00:03:12,678 --> 00:03:15,078
All traces of history still remain.

101
00:03:15,738 --> 00:03:17,008
(And also...)

102
00:03:17,348 --> 00:03:19,047
(the deep and rich Naju beef bone soup)

103
00:03:19,048 --> 00:03:21,718
You can also enjoy light and flavorful foods.

104
00:03:22,218 --> 00:03:23,647
A city where you want to remain.

105
00:03:23,648 --> 00:03:24,817
Naju in South Jeolla Province.

106
00:03:24,818 --> 00:03:26,158
- It's really nice.
- Naju.

107
00:03:26,188 --> 00:03:27,987
There's lots of good food here.

108
00:03:27,988 --> 00:03:29,057
Like what?

109
00:03:29,058 --> 00:03:30,358
- Beef bone soup.
- And?

110
00:03:30,528 --> 00:03:31,657
- Pears.
- Yes.

111
00:03:31,658 --> 00:03:33,757
You mentioned beef bone soup and pears.

112
00:03:33,758 --> 00:03:35,657
- Naju pears are famous.
- Yes.

113
00:03:35,658 --> 00:03:37,998
The concept of this trip is...

114
00:03:38,668 --> 00:03:40,637
Naju Trip Where Fun Is Multiplied.

115
00:03:40,638 --> 00:03:42,397
We must take a boat.

116
00:03:42,398 --> 00:03:44,107
- No.
- It means "many times."

117
00:03:44,108 --> 00:03:45,338
- Double.
- Two times.

118
00:03:45,768 --> 00:03:46,877
- Yes.
- Oh, that word.

119
00:03:46,878 --> 00:03:49,677
Take one each to start with.

120
00:03:49,678 --> 00:03:50,907
- Pass them on.
- Okay.

121
00:03:50,908 --> 00:03:52,578
- What's this for?
- I don't know.

122
00:03:52,918 --> 00:03:54,848
Everyone. On today's trip,

123
00:03:55,648 --> 00:03:57,487
we'll give you an allowance at the get go.

124
00:03:57,488 --> 00:03:58,848
Okay. Great.

125
00:03:59,018 --> 00:04:00,518
- What?
- We must write it down.

126
00:04:00,618 --> 00:04:02,357
- We get money now?
- Yes.

127
00:04:02,358 --> 00:04:05,288
Write down how much you want.

128
00:04:06,128 --> 00:04:08,758
We'll give you whatever you write down.

129
00:04:09,098 --> 00:04:10,767
Whatever we write? Something is off.

130
00:04:10,768 --> 00:04:11,968
What's the maximum amount?

131
00:04:12,298 --> 00:04:14,137
- We need a limit.
- Don't think of that for now.

132
00:04:14,138 --> 00:04:15,418
Can I write 100 million dollars?

133
00:04:15,908 --> 00:04:17,367
- One hundred million?
- We can write...

134
00:04:17,368 --> 00:04:18,567
- whatever we want?
- One billion?

135
00:04:18,568 --> 00:04:20,407
- Just enough for today.
- One billion?

136
00:04:20,408 --> 00:04:21,777
Shall we bankrupt KBS?

137
00:04:21,778 --> 00:04:22,947
Shall we?

138
00:04:22,948 --> 00:04:25,077
- I can write nines endlessly.
- How much is KBS worth?

139
00:04:25,078 --> 00:04:26,618
Can I retire my mom and dad?

140
00:04:26,718 --> 00:04:28,447
You don't all get the amount...

141
00:04:28,448 --> 00:04:30,118
- you write down.
- What?

142
00:04:30,318 --> 00:04:32,288
Out of the five amounts that you write,

143
00:04:32,688 --> 00:04:35,787
only the person who wrote the smallest amount gets paid.

144
00:04:35,788 --> 00:04:37,288
- Just one gets paid?
- Yes.

145
00:04:37,788 --> 00:04:39,427
- Okay.
- Each of us...

146
00:04:39,428 --> 00:04:41,727
- We must go large.
- Let's be smart.

147
00:04:41,728 --> 00:04:43,497
- Don't write a small amount...
- Share.

148
00:04:43,498 --> 00:04:45,168
- Let's share.
- Jong Min.

149
00:04:45,628 --> 00:04:46,797
He's weird. He's too into it.

150
00:04:46,798 --> 00:04:48,167
Don't anyone write ten dollars...

151
00:04:48,168 --> 00:04:49,437
for their own sake.

152
00:04:49,438 --> 00:04:51,107
If we go 100 million, 10 million,

153
00:04:51,108 --> 00:04:52,577
ten million, one million...

154
00:04:52,578 --> 00:04:53,837
- That would be insane.
- Yes.

155
00:04:53,838 --> 00:04:54,877
One million dollars...

156
00:04:54,878 --> 00:04:56,247
The minimum amount...

157
00:04:56,248 --> 00:04:57,407
Wouldn't one million work?

158
00:04:57,408 --> 00:04:59,278
What if you write down 300 dollars,

159
00:04:59,378 --> 00:05:00,847
and the rest of us put down 3,000 dollars?

160
00:05:00,848 --> 00:05:02,647
Yes. To be honest, 1,000 dollars is fine too.

161
00:05:02,648 --> 00:05:04,387
- We can eat well.
- We can feast...

162
00:05:04,388 --> 00:05:05,517
here in Naju.

163
00:05:05,518 --> 00:05:09,057
Spread out to write what you want, and then come back here.

164
00:05:09,058 --> 00:05:10,327
We won't get to discuss.

165
00:05:10,328 --> 00:05:12,458
I'll write the maximum amount.

166
00:05:12,558 --> 00:05:14,097
- I'll write a big number.
- The maximum amount.

167
00:05:14,098 --> 00:05:15,797
We need to write a big number.

168
00:05:15,798 --> 00:05:16,897
(They're all going all in!)

169
00:05:16,898 --> 00:05:18,627
- Spread out.
- Think of something.

170
00:05:18,628 --> 00:05:20,068
- Then...
- I'll write a big number.

171
00:05:20,938 --> 00:05:21,997
Hurry up.

172
00:05:21,998 --> 00:05:24,108
It has to be in the thousands of dollars range!

173
00:05:25,308 --> 00:05:26,537
Think wisely.

174
00:05:26,538 --> 00:05:28,638
- Seriously.
- We can eat at a convenience store.

175
00:05:29,008 --> 00:05:31,278
Ask the other directors what the others wrote.

176
00:05:32,148 --> 00:05:33,618
"How much did he put down?"

177
00:05:35,348 --> 00:05:38,318
I'm annoyingly convinced they'll go with 30 dollars or so.

178
00:05:39,718 --> 00:05:41,217
Enough for a bowl of beef bone soup?

179
00:05:41,218 --> 00:05:43,387
(A ten-dollar bowl of soup is Se Yoon's yardstick.)

180
00:05:43,388 --> 00:05:44,528
This is crazy.

181
00:05:44,928 --> 00:05:47,528
If I'm to win and buy the others cup noodles...

182
00:05:48,158 --> 00:05:50,028
Cup noodles is between 1.5 to 2 dollars.

183
00:05:50,868 --> 00:05:53,668
(Glancing warily)

184
00:05:55,298 --> 00:05:56,368
Shall I write two dollars?

185
00:05:56,838 --> 00:05:58,567
(The director laughs.)

186
00:05:58,568 --> 00:06:00,738
Ramyeon. That's all I need.

187
00:06:01,108 --> 00:06:03,077
No one here will write more than 100 dollars.

188
00:06:03,078 --> 00:06:04,078
(Deep distrust)

189
00:06:04,848 --> 00:06:06,777
(While acute Seon Ho ponders)

190
00:06:06,778 --> 00:06:09,118
How much should I write? What do you think?

191
00:06:10,288 --> 00:06:11,548
I'll go big!

192
00:06:12,488 --> 00:06:14,117
- What did he say?
- I'll go big!

193
00:06:14,118 --> 00:06:16,327
(Announcing for the N-th time that he'll go big.)

194
00:06:16,328 --> 00:06:18,458
Jong Min. How big will you go?

195
00:06:18,688 --> 00:06:19,997
Into the thousand dollar range.

196
00:06:19,998 --> 00:06:21,098
(1,000 dollars)

197
00:06:21,898 --> 00:06:25,527
(Will he bravely go with 1,000 dollars?)

198
00:06:25,528 --> 00:06:27,737
(Dollar)

199
00:06:27,738 --> 00:06:32,138
(How much did Jong Min, the person of interest write?)

200
00:06:34,238 --> 00:06:36,378
I saw. I saw it.

201
00:06:37,478 --> 00:06:39,107
- Are you insane?
- You saw mine?

202
00:06:39,108 --> 00:06:40,218
Have you lost your mind?

203
00:06:40,718 --> 00:06:42,118
Will you actually do this?

204
00:06:42,478 --> 00:06:43,688
- You saw it?
- I saw it.

205
00:06:43,848 --> 00:06:46,458
- He's cheating!
- I saw it.

206
00:06:46,558 --> 00:06:48,017
- He saw mine!
- Don't let him!

207
00:06:48,018 --> 00:06:49,357
- What...
- You should've hid it.

208
00:06:49,358 --> 00:06:51,958
Come on. He's over there. Can't you see this?

209
00:06:52,488 --> 00:06:53,958
Did he write two dollars?

210
00:06:54,898 --> 00:06:56,128
Does that say two dollars?

211
00:06:56,428 --> 00:06:58,628
What can you buy with two dollars?

212
00:06:58,898 --> 00:07:01,037
- He wrote how much?
- Two dollars.

213
00:07:01,038 --> 00:07:02,398
Are you kidding me?

214
00:07:02,908 --> 00:07:04,608
I have to write 1.5 dollars now.

215
00:07:06,138 --> 00:07:07,378
Who put down two dollars?

216
00:07:07,508 --> 00:07:09,378
- Someone wrote that amount?
- Jong Min.

217
00:07:09,548 --> 00:07:11,177
See? That's what he's like.

218
00:07:11,178 --> 00:07:12,347
I must go lower.

219
00:07:12,348 --> 00:07:13,617
(Less than the cost of ramyeon)

220
00:07:13,618 --> 00:07:15,978
- Darn it.
- Who would write two dollars?

221
00:07:16,148 --> 00:07:17,648
Why is he like that?

222
00:07:18,118 --> 00:07:19,618
I'm getting really annoyed.

223
00:07:20,018 --> 00:07:22,587
Jong Min. Add three zeroes to the end.

224
00:07:22,588 --> 00:07:23,987
(Change it to 2,000 dollars.)

225
00:07:23,988 --> 00:07:25,687
- Only then will I let you live.
- Okay.

226
00:07:25,688 --> 00:07:28,398
I think two dollars is too little.

227
00:07:28,728 --> 00:07:30,468
Two dollars is just unfair.

228
00:07:30,598 --> 00:07:32,168
Are we done? Darn it.

229
00:07:32,868 --> 00:07:34,368
Do you know what they call me?

230
00:07:35,198 --> 00:07:36,267
Loser Boy.

231
00:07:36,268 --> 00:07:38,508
(I go by Loser Boy.)

232
00:07:39,008 --> 00:07:42,238
(His nickname raises suspicion.)

233
00:07:42,378 --> 00:07:43,407
Let's gather around.

234
00:07:43,408 --> 00:07:45,878
- This shouldn't take this long.
- Right.

235
00:07:46,878 --> 00:07:48,178
Gosh, I was torn.

236
00:07:49,178 --> 00:07:50,448
I went with a big number.

237
00:07:51,218 --> 00:07:52,688
I wrote down a big number too.

238
00:07:53,758 --> 00:07:54,758
If you think...

239
00:07:55,358 --> 00:07:57,157
you wrote down the highest number, reveal it first.

240
00:07:57,158 --> 00:07:58,257
- I'll go first.
- Should I start...

241
00:07:58,258 --> 00:07:59,497
- I'll go first. Yes.
- You will?

242
00:07:59,498 --> 00:08:00,974
- Really?
- The thoughtful one should start.

243
00:08:00,998 --> 00:08:02,097
- The thoughtful celebrity.
- Yes.

244
00:08:02,098 --> 00:08:04,497
I didn't think that I would be able to win the money with this.

245
00:08:04,498 --> 00:08:05,597
I knew I couldn't.

246
00:08:05,598 --> 00:08:07,397
I wrote down number to help out my team. That was my mindset.

247
00:08:07,398 --> 00:08:08,737
- Of course. That's right.
- We're a team.

248
00:08:08,738 --> 00:08:10,467
- Right.
- I wrote down 2,000 dollars.

249
00:08:10,468 --> 00:08:11,767
(2,000 dollars)

250
00:08:11,768 --> 00:08:13,108
I wrote down a big number.

251
00:08:13,378 --> 00:08:14,838
It was for our team.

252
00:08:15,838 --> 00:08:17,847
(When he heard that Jong Min had wrote down 2 dollars, )

253
00:08:17,848 --> 00:08:20,718
(DinDin was furious.)

254
00:08:21,778 --> 00:08:24,418
(I don't think I can win this money.)

255
00:08:25,488 --> 00:08:29,757
(He suddenly went big with his bid.)

256
00:08:29,758 --> 00:08:31,398
I won't be able to win this money anyway.

257
00:08:32,028 --> 00:08:34,557
I went big with mine. It was for our team.

258
00:08:34,558 --> 00:08:35,997
Gosh, I feel so bad now.

259
00:08:35,998 --> 00:08:37,697
I made peace with not winning the money.

260
00:08:37,698 --> 00:08:38,797
- Isn't that number too high?
- If...

261
00:08:38,798 --> 00:08:41,467
If I were to lower my number and put down 1.5 dollars...

262
00:08:41,468 --> 00:08:43,007
- Right. You have a point.
- What's the point of winning it?

263
00:08:43,008 --> 00:08:45,337
- I bet mine is the next highest.
- I decided to go big for our team.

264
00:08:45,338 --> 00:08:47,218
- Okay. Let's check it.
- I'll reveal mine now.

265
00:08:47,308 --> 00:08:49,677
- I wrote down 120 dollars.
- That's a lot of money.

266
00:08:49,678 --> 00:08:50,907
Gukbap costs 12 dollars.

267
00:08:50,908 --> 00:08:53,017
If all of us want to have it for lunch and dinner,

268
00:08:53,018 --> 00:08:55,547
- we would need 120 dollars.
- So that's the gap?

269
00:08:55,548 --> 00:08:56,817
(The number dropped to one-tenth in a single turn.)

270
00:08:56,818 --> 00:08:58,417
- It dropped to a tenth.
- Check the next number.

271
00:08:58,418 --> 00:08:59,888
I bet we'll get double digits now.

272
00:09:00,058 --> 00:09:02,488
I'm sorry. It looks like it's between the three of us.

273
00:09:03,358 --> 00:09:06,898
One of us will be able to take this money.

274
00:09:07,528 --> 00:09:08,957
Who wants to go first?

275
00:09:08,958 --> 00:09:11,227
- Joon is quiet. I bet he won.
- All right.

276
00:09:11,228 --> 00:09:12,327
All right then.

277
00:09:12,328 --> 00:09:13,367
(Joon and Jong Min are oddly quiet.)

278
00:09:13,368 --> 00:09:15,097
Okay. Do you want to go first, Mr. Idiot?

279
00:09:15,098 --> 00:09:16,537
- Or should I go first?
- Well...

280
00:09:16,538 --> 00:09:17,858
(Se Yoon will reveal his number.)

281
00:09:18,068 --> 00:09:19,438
(Glancing)

282
00:09:22,908 --> 00:09:25,447
(It sort of looked like it said 1.5 dollars.)

283
00:09:25,448 --> 00:09:26,877
How much did you write down?

284
00:09:26,878 --> 00:09:28,077
(Slapping)

285
00:09:28,078 --> 00:09:30,018
- How much is it?
- Come on, 1.5 dollars?

286
00:09:30,248 --> 00:09:32,017
No, listen. I swear.

287
00:09:32,018 --> 00:09:33,817
- Hey.
- He wrote down 15 dollars.

288
00:09:33,818 --> 00:09:35,157
- It's 15 dollars.
- That's...

289
00:09:35,158 --> 00:09:36,358
- I swear.
- He's happy.

290
00:09:37,058 --> 00:09:38,327
You thought it was 1.5 dollars.

291
00:09:38,328 --> 00:09:40,158
But you're happy it's 15 dollars.

292
00:09:40,328 --> 00:09:41,358
(Laughing)

293
00:09:42,098 --> 00:09:43,698
Here's how my calculations went down.

294
00:09:44,068 --> 00:09:46,174
If I have to spend it alone, I'll have the beef bone soup.

295
00:09:46,198 --> 00:09:47,737
But if I can share the money with you,

296
00:09:47,738 --> 00:09:49,667
we can have cup noodles together. So I wrote down this number.

297
00:09:49,668 --> 00:09:50,838
By the way...

298
00:09:50,908 --> 00:09:53,508
(Now, it falls down to these two.)

299
00:09:53,808 --> 00:09:58,078
(Stingy Joon wanted to write down 2 dollars to have ramyeon alone.)

300
00:09:59,518 --> 00:10:03,217
(The loser promised to write down 20,000 dollars.)

301
00:10:03,218 --> 00:10:04,587
- Reveal it.
- Reveal it at the same time.

302
00:10:04,588 --> 00:10:06,758
- Reveal it. One, two, three.
- At the same time.

303
00:10:08,188 --> 00:10:09,727
- One, two, three.
- At the same time.

304
00:10:09,728 --> 00:10:12,087
(Joon's bid)

305
00:10:12,088 --> 00:10:14,428
(1.8 dollars)

306
00:10:14,758 --> 00:10:16,468
(Come on, is he serious?)

307
00:10:18,268 --> 00:10:20,238
(What about Jong Min?)

308
00:10:20,938 --> 00:10:22,297
(Jong Min's bid)

309
00:10:22,298 --> 00:10:24,967
(1.5 dollars)

310
00:10:24,968 --> 00:10:27,278
(1.5 dollars, 1.8 dollars)

311
00:10:28,208 --> 00:10:29,877
Yes!

312
00:10:29,878 --> 00:10:31,678
(Jong Min wins by 30 cents.)

313
00:10:32,508 --> 00:10:33,647
It's 1.5 dollars.

314
00:10:33,648 --> 00:10:35,048
(Speechless)

315
00:10:36,948 --> 00:10:38,218
I beat Joon.

316
00:10:39,048 --> 00:10:40,218
I beat Joon.

317
00:10:40,788 --> 00:10:42,018
Something feels off here.

318
00:10:42,928 --> 00:10:44,688
- I have a bad feeling about it.
- Jong Min.

319
00:10:45,458 --> 00:10:47,157
Could you tell us your intention?

320
00:10:47,158 --> 00:10:48,827
What are you going to do with 1.5 dollars?

321
00:10:48,828 --> 00:10:49,968
I'll eat ramyeon.

322
00:10:50,198 --> 00:10:52,227
What will you eat? The 1.5-dollar ramyeon?

323
00:10:52,228 --> 00:10:53,867
- This is disappointing...
- When I wrote down two dollars,

324
00:10:53,868 --> 00:10:55,598
you guys fell for it. Didn't you?

325
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:57,507
I lowered mine after hearing you wrote down two dollars.

326
00:10:57,508 --> 00:10:58,608
- Right?
- Yes.

327
00:10:59,208 --> 00:11:00,884
- So I lowered it to 1.5 dollars.
- You...

328
00:11:00,908 --> 00:11:02,407
Jong Min won the bid...

329
00:11:02,408 --> 00:11:03,977
since he wrote down the lowest number.

330
00:11:03,978 --> 00:11:04,978
- Here's your money.
- That pouch...

331
00:11:04,979 --> 00:11:06,524
- must cost more than the money.
- I'll do my best.

332
00:11:06,548 --> 00:11:08,317
Jong Min, the pouch must cost more.

333
00:11:08,318 --> 00:11:09,817
- You can sell it for two dollars.
- Jong Min.

334
00:11:09,818 --> 00:11:12,118
- I bet the markers cost more.
- Right.

335
00:11:12,348 --> 00:11:13,957
Yes. I feel so safe now.

336
00:11:13,958 --> 00:11:15,187
(He's the only one who feels safe.)

337
00:11:15,188 --> 00:11:16,357
Only 1.5 dollars?

338
00:11:16,358 --> 00:11:17,428
Everyone.

339
00:11:17,688 --> 00:11:20,797
Today's trip is called Naju Trip Where Fun Is Multiplied.

340
00:11:20,798 --> 00:11:22,358
- Will we get to grow our money?
- Yes.

341
00:11:22,498 --> 00:11:24,828
This will be a team match today.

342
00:11:25,068 --> 00:11:27,198
- This was our first game then.
- Exactly.

343
00:11:27,498 --> 00:11:31,537
(It will be a team match, not an individual match.)

344
00:11:31,538 --> 00:11:32,937
- Then our initial capital...
- Come on.

345
00:11:32,938 --> 00:11:34,337
Will be only 1.5 dollars?

346
00:11:34,338 --> 00:11:35,407
Yes.

347
00:11:35,408 --> 00:11:38,107
(Oh, it was going to be a team match?)

348
00:11:38,108 --> 00:11:39,747
You will be growing...

349
00:11:39,748 --> 00:11:41,777
your allowance while traveling Naju today.

350
00:11:41,778 --> 00:11:42,848
Yes!

351
00:11:44,018 --> 00:11:46,187
(Seriously? What's wrong with that guy?)

352
00:11:46,188 --> 00:11:47,518
He said we could grow our money.

353
00:11:48,258 --> 00:11:50,427
We can start small in the beginning. You know?

354
00:11:50,428 --> 00:11:52,558
He's annoyed too.

355
00:11:52,788 --> 00:11:55,658
"What? Then should I have written down 1,000 dollars?"

356
00:11:56,228 --> 00:11:57,988
You didn't tell us it would be a team match.

357
00:11:58,328 --> 00:12:00,008
I thought it would be an individual match.

358
00:12:00,968 --> 00:12:03,437
You'll be able to grow your allowance.

359
00:12:03,438 --> 00:12:05,038
With the allowance you earned,

360
00:12:05,108 --> 00:12:07,507
you will have to pay for your lunch.

361
00:12:07,508 --> 00:12:08,678
With 1.5 dollars?

362
00:12:09,308 --> 00:12:11,277
- We can still try to grow it.
- My gosh.

363
00:12:11,278 --> 00:12:13,477
That's right. The money we gave to Jong Min...

364
00:12:13,478 --> 00:12:15,447
will be your initial capital.

365
00:12:15,448 --> 00:12:16,518
Let's do it.

366
00:12:16,888 --> 00:12:18,217
Don't return the sketchbook. Let's sell it later.

367
00:12:18,218 --> 00:12:19,547
(We'll sell it if we run out of money.)

368
00:12:19,548 --> 00:12:21,508
Don't give them the marker either. We never know.

369
00:12:22,158 --> 00:12:25,088
Your first random game to win more allowance is called...

370
00:12:25,258 --> 00:12:27,298
Grab It to Survive.

371
00:12:27,398 --> 00:12:29,927
- Grab It to Survive.
- As you jump rope,

372
00:12:29,928 --> 00:12:32,398
you have to pick up as much money as you want.

373
00:12:33,338 --> 00:12:35,337
But you must get out without tripping...

374
00:12:35,338 --> 00:12:38,368
with the money you collected. Only then will the money count.

375
00:12:38,808 --> 00:12:40,007
- That won't be easy.
- Let's say you grabbed two dollars.

376
00:12:40,008 --> 00:12:41,777
If you trip as you're about to grab three dollars,

377
00:12:41,778 --> 00:12:42,877
- your total will be zero.
- You'll take everything away?

378
00:12:42,878 --> 00:12:44,398
- We can't win any money then.
- Gosh.

379
00:12:44,578 --> 00:12:46,517
- This will be hard then.
- It won't be easy.

380
00:12:46,518 --> 00:12:47,877
It's all or nothing.

381
00:12:47,878 --> 00:12:49,718
Shouldn't Se Yoon go first?

382
00:12:49,848 --> 00:12:52,564
- So start with the trash card?
- We must play the trash card first.

383
00:12:52,588 --> 00:12:55,457
It's sad that you're calling me the trash card. Okay. I'll go first.

384
00:12:55,458 --> 00:12:57,788
Let's try to grab ten dollars each.

385
00:12:57,928 --> 00:12:59,757
- We can buy lunch with 50 dollars.
- That's pretty nice.

386
00:12:59,758 --> 00:13:01,557
So our goal is grabbing ten dollars each.

387
00:13:01,558 --> 00:13:04,267
Guys, we'll give you gloves just in case your hands get cold.

388
00:13:04,268 --> 00:13:05,268
What are you doing?

389
00:13:05,269 --> 00:13:06,767
- My hands aren't cold.
- What's that? We're fine.

390
00:13:06,768 --> 00:13:07,797
We're all right.

391
00:13:07,798 --> 00:13:09,497
We can't pick up anything with the oven mitts.

392
00:13:09,498 --> 00:13:10,858
The paper slips are on the ground.

393
00:13:12,038 --> 00:13:13,907
- We'll give you pretty ones.
- How can we do this with them on?

394
00:13:13,908 --> 00:13:16,208
Are you kidding me? Is that what you got for us?

395
00:13:16,278 --> 00:13:17,447
To make things harder for us?

396
00:13:17,448 --> 00:13:18,607
- By the way, can I take them...
- This is crazy.

397
00:13:18,608 --> 00:13:19,717
After the shoot?

398
00:13:19,718 --> 00:13:21,248
- I need oven mitts at home.
- Okay.

399
00:13:21,818 --> 00:13:23,217
- Hey, these mitts are cute.
- I want this one.

400
00:13:23,218 --> 00:13:25,048
I bet the oven mitts cost 1.5 dollars.

401
00:13:26,088 --> 00:13:27,757
- They're expensive.
- Really?

402
00:13:27,758 --> 00:13:28,987
- The paper...
- How can we grab it with these on?

403
00:13:28,988 --> 00:13:31,258
- How can we do this?
- Hey, this is impossible.

404
00:13:31,658 --> 00:13:33,027
- Let's go.
- Yes. Let's go.

405
00:13:33,028 --> 00:13:34,358
No. This can't be easy.

406
00:13:34,628 --> 00:13:36,667
Let's begin. Okay. Start turning the rope.

407
00:13:36,668 --> 00:13:38,598
- Se Yoon. Go.
- Let's do this.

408
00:13:39,568 --> 00:13:41,544
- Gosh, this isn't easy.
- Se Yoon, keep watching.

409
00:13:41,568 --> 00:13:42,698
Let's go.

410
00:13:42,998 --> 00:13:44,637
- I see a five-dollar one.
- You can do this.

411
00:13:44,638 --> 00:13:45,867
- Try to last as long as possible.
- I see a five-dollar one!

412
00:13:45,868 --> 00:13:47,907
I'd call it a success if you can grab five dollars.

413
00:13:47,908 --> 00:13:50,748
- Grabbing 2 of the 5-dollar ones...
- Try to last as long as possible.

414
00:13:52,308 --> 00:13:53,377
(He steps in without tripping on the rope.)

415
00:13:53,378 --> 00:13:55,017
I'd call it a success if you can grab five dollars.

416
00:13:55,018 --> 00:13:56,948
- That's good.
- Se Yoon, come on out!

417
00:13:57,088 --> 00:13:58,847
I'd call it a success if you can grab five dollars.

418
00:13:58,848 --> 00:14:00,594
(He successfully snatches up the money surprisingly fast.)

419
00:14:00,618 --> 00:14:01,757
That's good.

420
00:14:01,758 --> 00:14:03,328
- Se Yoon, come on out!
- Come out.

421
00:14:03,558 --> 00:14:05,428
(Nagging him to step out)

422
00:14:05,558 --> 00:14:07,258
- I told you to come out!
- Come out.

423
00:14:08,398 --> 00:14:09,528
- Come on out!
- Come out.

424
00:14:09,828 --> 00:14:13,028
(The fatty flies!)

425
00:14:14,298 --> 00:14:18,268
(His greed gets the better of him and ruins his chance.)

426
00:14:19,568 --> 00:14:20,678
Gosh, he got greedy.

427
00:14:21,538 --> 00:14:22,608
(Laughing)

428
00:14:23,608 --> 00:14:26,047
- I told you to...
- I told you not to get greedy.

429
00:14:26,048 --> 00:14:28,148
I told you to step out right away.

430
00:14:29,018 --> 00:14:31,818
Why did you fall down in the most embarrassing way?

431
00:14:31,918 --> 00:14:32,918
(Laughing)

432
00:14:33,418 --> 00:14:34,517
Don't look at him.

433
00:14:34,518 --> 00:14:37,988
Even if you tried, it wouldn't have been two dollars.

434
00:14:38,188 --> 00:14:39,558
- This is crazy.
- Hey.

435
00:14:40,358 --> 00:14:41,957
Hey, some of them have a negative sign.

436
00:14:41,958 --> 00:14:44,167
- Some of them have a negative sign.
- Negative numbers?

437
00:14:44,168 --> 00:14:45,888
- A negative sign.
- You can't see it well.

438
00:14:45,968 --> 00:14:47,237
- Are you serious?
- You can't see it well.

439
00:14:47,238 --> 00:14:49,358
- There's a negative sign?
- There's a negative sign?

440
00:14:49,398 --> 00:14:51,867
We have to be careful. There's a negative sign.

441
00:14:51,868 --> 00:14:53,677
- Do a good job.
- Just grab ten dollars.

442
00:14:53,678 --> 00:14:55,977
- Let's just grab 10 dollars.
- That one is minus 5 dollars.

443
00:14:55,978 --> 00:14:57,577
- A ten-dollar one is in the middle.
- Show us.

444
00:14:57,578 --> 00:14:58,578
Grab ten dollars and step out.

445
00:14:58,579 --> 00:15:00,847
- Be careful with your back.
- Okay.

446
00:15:00,848 --> 00:15:02,247
- His jumps are so much better.
- Ten dollars.

447
00:15:02,248 --> 00:15:03,368
- That's it.
- There you go.

448
00:15:03,648 --> 00:15:05,017
- There you go.
- Step out.

449
00:15:05,018 --> 00:15:06,487
- That's it.
- Step out now.

450
00:15:06,488 --> 00:15:07,517
- That's it. Ten dollars.
- Step out now.

451
00:15:07,518 --> 00:15:09,387
(He grabs a handful.)

452
00:15:09,388 --> 00:15:10,388
- That's it. Ten dollars.
- There you go.

453
00:15:10,389 --> 00:15:11,457
- Step out.
- There you go.

454
00:15:11,458 --> 00:15:12,887
- Step out.
- No, I can keep going.

455
00:15:12,888 --> 00:15:14,597
- You can keep going?
- Don't get greedy.

456
00:15:14,598 --> 00:15:16,257
- Step out.
- Don't get greedy.

457
00:15:16,258 --> 00:15:17,327
- Seon Ho, step out.
- What are you doing?

458
00:15:17,328 --> 00:15:18,527
- Go for it.
- You...

459
00:15:18,528 --> 00:15:19,998
- Hey.
- Hey.

460
00:15:21,268 --> 00:15:22,968
- Hey! Step out.
- Okay.

461
00:15:23,308 --> 00:15:25,507
(His two hands are getting full thanks to his amazing performance.)

462
00:15:25,508 --> 00:15:26,638
Come on out.

463
00:15:26,708 --> 00:15:27,937
(That's great!)

464
00:15:27,938 --> 00:15:30,177
- Step out now!
- Gosh.

465
00:15:30,178 --> 00:15:32,047
- Just step out now.
- Come on out.

466
00:15:32,048 --> 00:15:33,177
- Step out.
- That's good now.

467
00:15:33,178 --> 00:15:34,577
(Wait. Let me go for it one more time.)

468
00:15:34,578 --> 00:15:36,247
- That's good.
- Don't try to overcompensate.

469
00:15:36,248 --> 00:15:37,447
Just step out!

470
00:15:37,448 --> 00:15:38,488
You...

471
00:15:38,748 --> 00:15:39,987
(What?)

472
00:15:39,988 --> 00:15:41,058
(Seon Ho...)

473
00:15:41,888 --> 00:15:43,087
(He's totally doomed due to his greed.)

474
00:15:43,088 --> 00:15:44,358
I told you to step out!

475
00:15:44,528 --> 00:15:47,058
(Come on. I told you to step out!)

476
00:15:47,428 --> 00:15:49,357
(Angrily kicking at him)

477
00:15:49,358 --> 00:15:50,897
- Why did you do that?
- You're making me mad.

478
00:15:50,898 --> 00:15:52,267
- I saw five dollars.
- How much...

479
00:15:52,268 --> 00:15:53,837
- How much was it?
- I told you to step out.

480
00:15:53,838 --> 00:15:55,067
Had you stepped out...

481
00:15:55,068 --> 00:15:56,468
None of these have a negative sign.

482
00:15:56,608 --> 00:15:57,837
We could've won 11.5 dollars.

483
00:15:57,838 --> 00:15:59,908
I told you to step out right then.

484
00:15:59,938 --> 00:16:02,537
If you learned anything from me, you should have stepped out.

485
00:16:02,538 --> 00:16:04,108
My greed got the better of me.

486
00:16:04,478 --> 00:16:06,347
This is crazy. You lost 11.5 dollars.

487
00:16:06,348 --> 00:16:08,354
- This was a lot of money.
- This is driving me crazy.

488
00:16:08,378 --> 00:16:10,387
- It's so frustrating.
- How frustrating.

489
00:16:10,388 --> 00:16:11,617
- Hey, just grab ten dollars.
- So...

490
00:16:11,618 --> 00:16:13,487
- Step out when you grab some money.
- Let's begin right away.

491
00:16:13,488 --> 00:16:14,587
(A sly trick of overlapping the money)

492
00:16:14,588 --> 00:16:17,327
- Here.
- He's overlapping the money.

493
00:16:17,328 --> 00:16:18,487
- Grab that.
- Okay. Great.

494
00:16:18,488 --> 00:16:19,998
- What was that?
- What did you do?

495
00:16:20,128 --> 00:16:22,257
(Fixing it right away)

496
00:16:22,258 --> 00:16:24,897
- What? Come on. That's not right.
- What is this?

497
00:16:24,898 --> 00:16:26,198
What's gotten into you?

498
00:16:26,868 --> 00:16:28,567
- He's on our side.
- Why are you working so hard?

499
00:16:28,568 --> 00:16:30,367
- Who's next?
- It's Joon.

500
00:16:30,368 --> 00:16:31,437
- Go for it, Joon.
- Just grab ten dollars.

501
00:16:31,438 --> 00:16:33,158
- Grab that and come out.
- Seriously. Yes.

502
00:16:33,908 --> 00:16:36,948
(Let me handle all the physical games.)

503
00:16:37,208 --> 00:16:39,917
(We're counting on you, Joon.)

504
00:16:39,918 --> 00:16:41,978
- Just grab ten dollars.
- Okay.

505
00:16:42,118 --> 00:16:44,248
- Where is it?
- It's right under your right foot.

506
00:16:44,388 --> 00:16:46,248
(It's right under your right foot.)

507
00:16:46,758 --> 00:16:48,288
(Checking the location)

508
00:16:48,618 --> 00:16:50,588
Come on. This is so annoying.

509
00:16:51,128 --> 00:16:53,698
- That's it.
- Come on. This is so annoying.

510
00:16:54,158 --> 00:16:55,958
What are you guys doing?

511
00:16:56,558 --> 00:16:58,398
(Come on, are you kidding me?)

512
00:16:58,498 --> 00:17:00,498
(Cursing him out with his gaze)

513
00:17:00,598 --> 00:17:01,697
What is this?

514
00:17:01,698 --> 00:17:03,698
He's the one who messed up. Why take it out on me?

515
00:17:04,308 --> 00:17:06,268
- Only two of you are left to go.
- Hold on.

516
00:17:06,708 --> 00:17:08,708
What do I do? I'm so sorry.

517
00:17:09,338 --> 00:17:11,978
- I really tried my best.
- It's okay.

518
00:17:12,208 --> 00:17:14,817
(Cursing him)

519
00:17:14,818 --> 00:17:16,117
- Who still hasn't gone yet?
- Me.

520
00:17:16,118 --> 00:17:17,817
- All the way over there.
- I messed up...

521
00:17:17,818 --> 00:17:19,187
when I tried to look for the ten-dollar one.

522
00:17:19,188 --> 00:17:20,687
- Don't look for it. Just grab it.
- Hey, keep looking at it.

523
00:17:20,688 --> 00:17:22,517
(Show us what you got, Mr. Clever.)

524
00:17:22,518 --> 00:17:23,827
- Keep looking.
- Don't look for it. Just grab it.

525
00:17:23,828 --> 00:17:25,687
- You must look at the rope.
- If you do, you'll end up like me.

526
00:17:25,688 --> 00:17:27,358
That's good. Go. Step out!

527
00:17:27,458 --> 00:17:28,897
- What?
- What?

528
00:17:28,898 --> 00:17:31,074
- If you do, you'll end up like me.
- That's good. Go. Step out!

529
00:17:31,098 --> 00:17:33,228
(They finally win money for the first time.)

530
00:17:33,498 --> 00:17:34,997
- How much is it?
- It's ten dollars.

531
00:17:34,998 --> 00:17:36,167
- Ten dollars.
- I knew it.

532
00:17:36,168 --> 00:17:38,237
- This is what you should've done.
- He's the wisest one among us.

533
00:17:38,238 --> 00:17:40,007
- Well done.
- Should we have done that?

534
00:17:40,008 --> 00:17:42,014
- This is what you should've done.
- Good job. You have my support.

535
00:17:42,038 --> 00:17:43,307
If all of us did this,

536
00:17:43,308 --> 00:17:44,677
we could've gotten ten dollars each.

537
00:17:44,678 --> 00:17:45,707
- Yes.
- Jong Min.

538
00:17:45,708 --> 00:17:46,717
- You're the last one.
- The oven mitts.

539
00:17:46,718 --> 00:17:47,718
- Jong Min.
- Jong Min.

540
00:17:47,719 --> 00:17:49,047
Show us, Jong Min.

541
00:17:49,048 --> 00:17:51,448
I see a pile of five-dollar paper slips over there.

542
00:17:51,618 --> 00:17:54,118
- I know.
- Hurry up. Step in.

543
00:17:54,788 --> 00:17:56,117
That's it. It's right under you now.

544
00:17:56,118 --> 00:17:57,657
- Go.
- It's right under you.

545
00:17:57,658 --> 00:17:58,887
- Where?
- It's under you.

546
00:17:58,888 --> 00:18:00,488
- Be calm.
- It's under your right foot.

547
00:18:00,728 --> 00:18:01,857
- It's under your right foot.
- Stay calm.

548
00:18:01,858 --> 00:18:02,897
- Jong Min.
- That's it.

549
00:18:02,898 --> 00:18:03,927
- There.
- That's it.

550
00:18:03,928 --> 00:18:04,928
Jump.

551
00:18:05,328 --> 00:18:07,368
(He manages to grab them.)

552
00:18:07,898 --> 00:18:10,467
- Jump.
- It's under your right foot.

553
00:18:10,468 --> 00:18:11,837
- It's under your right foot.
- Jump. Move back.

554
00:18:11,838 --> 00:18:13,638
- There you go. Step out.
- Step out.

555
00:18:14,238 --> 00:18:15,407
(He quickly snatches it up...)

556
00:18:15,408 --> 00:18:17,347
(and just barely avoids the rope.)

557
00:18:17,348 --> 00:18:18,348
Move back.

558
00:18:18,349 --> 00:18:20,278
(He obtains a whopping 5 dollars.)

559
00:18:20,578 --> 00:18:22,778
(You just have to step out now.)

560
00:18:23,178 --> 00:18:26,603
(All there is left for him to do is to leave without tripping.)

561
00:18:26,697 --> 00:18:27,469
- It's under your right foot.
- Move back.

562
00:18:27,494 --> 00:18:29,493
- There you go. Step out.
- Step out.

563
00:18:29,494 --> 00:18:31,223
- Step out.
- Step out.

564
00:18:31,224 --> 00:18:32,794
- Where did it go?
- My gosh.

565
00:18:33,064 --> 00:18:35,334
(After all that effort to grab it, he lets it get away.)

566
00:18:35,694 --> 00:18:37,163
(Flustered)

567
00:18:37,164 --> 00:18:38,604
- Why did you lose it?
- He lost it.

568
00:18:38,664 --> 00:18:40,073
(Darn it!)

569
00:18:40,074 --> 00:18:42,234
Why did you grab one with a negative number?

570
00:18:42,734 --> 00:18:45,244
(He grabbed minus 1-dollar slip after all that.)

571
00:18:45,444 --> 00:18:46,444
(Today isn't my day.)

572
00:18:46,445 --> 00:18:47,544
That has a negative sign?

573
00:18:47,874 --> 00:18:49,714
- What is this?
- I had it right here.

574
00:18:50,044 --> 00:18:51,983
- This is driving me crazy.
- I had it in my left hand.

575
00:18:51,984 --> 00:18:53,054
(Feeling hollow)

576
00:18:53,814 --> 00:18:56,174
- Gosh, this is crazy.
- They're a tough team to play with.

577
00:18:56,284 --> 00:18:58,053
I should've stepped out. Why did I see the five-dollar one?

578
00:18:58,054 --> 00:18:59,283
We have 10.5 dollars then.

579
00:18:59,284 --> 00:19:00,823
All right, everyone.

580
00:19:00,824 --> 00:19:03,763
DinDin won ten dollars from his turn.

581
00:19:03,764 --> 00:19:04,764
- Great job.
- And...

582
00:19:04,765 --> 00:19:06,833
Jong Min grabbed minus one dollar.

583
00:19:06,834 --> 00:19:08,193
- You won nine dollars.
- We did well.

584
00:19:08,194 --> 00:19:09,933
- We have 10.5 dollars.
- We did well.

585
00:19:09,934 --> 00:19:11,263
Our allowance is 10.5 dollars.

586
00:19:11,264 --> 00:19:12,634
- Yes!
- I'm sorry to say this.

587
00:19:12,764 --> 00:19:14,524
But I'm the only one who actually won money.

588
00:19:14,734 --> 00:19:16,503
- Right.
- Don't say, "We did well."

589
00:19:16,504 --> 00:19:18,464
- DinDin did well.
- Clap three times for DinDin.

590
00:19:18,704 --> 00:19:20,373
- Okay.
- Don't clap a lot for him.

591
00:19:20,374 --> 00:19:22,173
- We made a lot of money.
- Yes, we're just starting.

592
00:19:22,174 --> 00:19:23,913
- You have more games to play.
- Okay.

593
00:19:23,914 --> 00:19:24,914
- Really?
- Yes.

594
00:19:24,915 --> 00:19:26,483
We're off to a great start.

595
00:19:26,484 --> 00:19:27,713
- Okay.
- It's going well.

596
00:19:27,714 --> 00:19:29,954
- Let's go to our next spot.
- Okay.

597
00:19:30,124 --> 00:19:31,924
We are your meal companion for Sunday dinner.

598
00:19:32,454 --> 00:19:34,824
Naju Trip Where Fun Is Multiplied...

599
00:19:35,354 --> 00:19:37,324
- Will begin now.
- Who are we?

600
00:19:37,624 --> 00:19:38,693
2 Days...

601
00:19:38,694 --> 00:19:40,634
- 1 Night!
- 1 Night!

602
00:19:41,794 --> 00:19:42,933
"Who are we?"

603
00:19:42,934 --> 00:19:44,464
(What kind of trip awaits them today?)

604
00:19:44,764 --> 00:19:47,274
It's been a while since we got to drive this car.

605
00:19:47,674 --> 00:19:49,774
My goodness. You know what?

606
00:19:50,074 --> 00:19:52,103
We won ten dollars thanks to DinDin.

607
00:19:52,104 --> 00:19:53,313
- Right.
- No, wait.

608
00:19:53,314 --> 00:19:54,714
Jong Min grabbed a dollar too.

609
00:19:54,844 --> 00:19:56,713
- Right.
- He grabbed minus one dollar.

610
00:19:56,714 --> 00:19:58,983
So we have 10.5 dollars now?

611
00:19:58,984 --> 00:20:00,260
- We have 10.5 dollars.
- We have 10.5 dollars.

612
00:20:00,284 --> 00:20:02,453
- How much is beef bone soup?
- It's 12 dollars.

613
00:20:02,454 --> 00:20:04,054
It's between 12 and 15 dollars.

614
00:20:04,184 --> 00:20:05,383
- Then...
- Usually.

615
00:20:05,384 --> 00:20:07,753
- We need 75 to 80 dollars.
- Yes.

616
00:20:07,754 --> 00:20:09,223
We need at least 80 dollars.

617
00:20:09,224 --> 00:20:10,863
- The 6 of us... The 5 of us...
- That's a safe number.

618
00:20:10,864 --> 00:20:13,094
Hear me out. At the last game...

619
00:20:13,834 --> 00:20:16,093
Starring on this show after a survival competition show...

620
00:20:16,094 --> 00:20:17,634
isn't an easy transition.

621
00:20:18,764 --> 00:20:21,034
I was up against a KAIST graduate.

622
00:20:21,334 --> 00:20:23,703
You guys don't seem to be on the same level as me.

623
00:20:23,704 --> 00:20:25,243
They said we had to jump rope.

624
00:20:25,244 --> 00:20:27,273
Logically speaking, we just had to grab one and step out.

625
00:20:27,274 --> 00:20:29,690
But guys like Seon Ho get greedy and end up wasting his chance.

626
00:20:29,714 --> 00:20:31,213
- I can't stop thinking about it.
- If you guys didn't get greedy,

627
00:20:31,214 --> 00:20:33,083
- we could've had 70 dollars by now.
- Right.

628
00:20:33,084 --> 00:20:34,354
We shouldn't get greedy.

629
00:20:34,554 --> 00:20:36,424
- You needed to be a bit greedy.
- Really?

630
00:20:37,754 --> 00:20:39,653
My gosh. Joon just stepped on the rope.

631
00:20:39,654 --> 00:20:41,193
- He just did a bad job.
- Joon...

632
00:20:41,194 --> 00:20:43,394
He was born to do better with that nice body of his.

633
00:20:44,394 --> 00:20:46,224
Messing it up was my thing. But he joined me.

634
00:20:46,794 --> 00:20:47,993
Let's not get greedy.

635
00:20:47,994 --> 00:20:49,903
- Let's go one step at a time.
- Yes. Let's just do our part.

636
00:20:49,904 --> 00:20:51,703
Let's try to earn at least ten dollars per game.

637
00:20:51,704 --> 00:20:53,173
- That should be our mindset.
- Yes.

638
00:20:53,174 --> 00:20:54,833
- Yes.
- Let's eat beef bone soup.

639
00:20:54,834 --> 00:20:56,004
- Okay.
- Okay. That's good.

640
00:20:57,004 --> 00:20:59,274
The cherry blossoms are falling now.

641
00:20:59,774 --> 00:21:00,943
- They're already...
- Well, yes.

642
00:21:00,944 --> 00:21:02,844
- They fell after the rain.
- Yes, it rained.

643
00:21:03,244 --> 00:21:05,943
My gosh. It would've been so pretty if we came during the full bloom.

644
00:21:05,944 --> 00:21:11,654
(Cherry blossoms' brief season makes them look more beautiful.)

645
00:21:13,724 --> 00:21:14,993
(Singing spring songs even the cherry blossoms are falling.)

646
00:21:14,994 --> 00:21:16,223
- It's "Cherry Blossom Ending."
- Gosh.

647
00:21:16,224 --> 00:21:17,393
- In spring, - Right.

648
00:21:17,394 --> 00:21:19,933
- he gets a lot more royalties.
- Right.

649
00:21:19,934 --> 00:21:21,634
I have a spring song too.

650
00:21:21,964 --> 00:21:24,063
- What is it?
- In my opinion, it's...

651
00:21:24,064 --> 00:21:27,033
one of my undiscovered gems. It's my favorite song.

652
00:21:27,034 --> 00:21:28,203
Tell us the title.

653
00:21:28,204 --> 00:21:29,533
"Foolin' Myself."

654
00:21:29,534 --> 00:21:30,873
I bet your song is playing now.

655
00:21:30,874 --> 00:21:33,174
- Of course, I know the song.
- I know it too.

656
00:21:33,414 --> 00:21:35,473
(Acknowledging it as a hidden gem)

657
00:21:35,474 --> 00:21:37,114
I really love this song.

658
00:21:37,584 --> 00:21:40,384
This is the kind of feeling I get when the weather warms up.

659
00:21:40,654 --> 00:21:42,983
Well, the best song to listen to in spring would be...

660
00:21:42,984 --> 00:21:45,524
Bookku Ddoong's song, "Fool" featuring Choi Yoo Jung.

661
00:21:46,054 --> 00:21:47,423
- When you look at flowers...
- "Fool?"

662
00:21:47,424 --> 00:21:49,193
- It's a spring song?
- Yes.

663
00:21:49,194 --> 00:21:50,623
- That's a great song.
- What's "Fool?"

664
00:21:50,624 --> 00:21:51,723
I've never heard of it.

665
00:21:51,724 --> 00:21:52,724
(Flustered by the buzzkill)

666
00:21:52,725 --> 00:21:54,064
- I know the song.
- Yes.

667
00:21:54,734 --> 00:21:56,164
Yoo Jung, you're doing well. Right?

668
00:21:56,294 --> 00:21:58,104
I have a spring song too.

669
00:21:58,464 --> 00:21:59,974
The title is "Maybe Spring."

670
00:22:00,234 --> 00:22:01,473
"Maybe Spring" by Yoo Seon Ho?

671
00:22:01,474 --> 00:22:03,803
- Are you a singer?
- I released a song.

672
00:22:03,804 --> 00:22:05,303
Come to think of it, I released a song.

673
00:22:05,304 --> 00:22:07,443
- I released a spring song.
- Can you sing a snippet?

674
00:22:07,444 --> 00:22:08,473
- Sing it.
- Sing it.

675
00:22:08,474 --> 00:22:13,353
(I'll hold your beautiful hand and keep it warm every day)

676
00:22:13,354 --> 00:22:14,683
Do you sing that before going into the cold water?

677
00:22:14,684 --> 00:22:16,764
(Do you sing that before going into the cold water?)

678
00:22:17,024 --> 00:22:19,254
(A new way of singing, the cold water method)

679
00:22:19,624 --> 00:22:20,654
(Laughing)

680
00:22:21,424 --> 00:22:24,094
(Mocking him)

681
00:22:24,194 --> 00:22:27,464
Did you record the song at a sauna? Or in the cold bathtub?

682
00:22:27,994 --> 00:22:29,464
(Joining Se Yoon to mock him)

683
00:22:29,864 --> 00:22:30,904
(Laughing)

684
00:22:31,864 --> 00:22:34,734
(They take teasing their senior seriously.)

685
00:22:37,704 --> 00:22:38,873
That's how I should promote songs.

686
00:22:38,874 --> 00:22:41,374
I'm getting curious, so I want to listen to it.

687
00:22:41,714 --> 00:22:43,884
- The song...
- I'm curious about the song.

688
00:22:43,984 --> 00:22:48,253
(He didn't mean it, but he effectively promotes his song.)

689
00:22:48,254 --> 00:22:49,683
How does the original version sound?

690
00:22:49,684 --> 00:22:51,353
(They arrive at the next spot in no time.)

691
00:22:51,354 --> 00:22:53,894
There are all kinds of spring songs.

692
00:22:54,154 --> 00:22:55,894
I really want to listen to Seon Ho's song.

693
00:22:56,154 --> 00:22:58,364
- Let's go, guys.
- Let's go and make money.

694
00:23:00,134 --> 00:23:01,193
This place looks amazing. Where are we?

695
00:23:01,194 --> 00:23:04,063
Is this the Sikpaktakur Road?

696
00:23:04,064 --> 00:23:05,904
- Metasequoia-lined Road?
- Yes. I meant that.

697
00:23:05,964 --> 00:23:07,104
Smell it.

698
00:23:07,834 --> 00:23:09,903
- Inhale deeply through your nose.
- This is nice.

699
00:23:09,904 --> 00:23:12,264
(The trail with metasequoia trees stretches out to no end.)

700
00:23:13,244 --> 00:23:15,273
- Oh, my. It's so picturesque.
- I love it here.

701
00:23:15,274 --> 00:23:17,013
(The towering trees exude a sense of grandeur and comfort.)

702
00:23:17,014 --> 00:23:19,020
(The towering trees exude a sense of grandeur and comfort.)

703
00:23:19,044 --> 00:23:20,353
(With each changing season, )

704
00:23:20,354 --> 00:23:22,060
(they put on a new set of beautiful colors.)

705
00:23:22,084 --> 00:23:27,954
(A place where you can fully enjoy the lush greenery of summer)

706
00:23:28,754 --> 00:23:30,293
Gosh, this place is indeed picturesque.

707
00:23:30,294 --> 00:23:32,524
- Yes. This is...
- This place looks so cool.

708
00:23:33,064 --> 00:23:34,894
- I love it here.
- Yes, it's so nice.

709
00:23:35,534 --> 00:23:37,163
- It's beautiful.
- The air is fresh.

710
00:23:37,164 --> 00:23:38,903
- Are they metasequoia trees?
- Metasequoia trees.

711
00:23:38,904 --> 00:23:40,633
This is so cool. Stand there.

712
00:23:40,634 --> 00:23:42,603
(We ought to take pictures at a cool place like this.)

713
00:23:42,604 --> 00:23:44,174
Jong Min is acting like a dad today.

714
00:23:45,804 --> 00:23:47,114
Maybe, he became one.

715
00:23:47,914 --> 00:23:48,914
(Not yet!)

716
00:23:48,915 --> 00:23:49,944
Okay.

717
00:23:51,044 --> 00:23:52,513
Jong Min. Let me take a picture of you too.

718
00:23:52,514 --> 00:23:55,154
(You can't help but take pictures at this photo spot.)

719
00:23:56,054 --> 00:23:58,223
- Good.
- We have to take pictures here.

720
00:23:58,224 --> 00:23:59,624
- What a great picture.
- You know?

721
00:24:00,354 --> 00:24:02,454
You got a message. Your wife bought something.

722
00:24:04,424 --> 00:24:05,593
His facial expression...

723
00:24:05,594 --> 00:24:06,693
(My wife bought something with my card.)

724
00:24:06,694 --> 00:24:07,764
(Clenching his teeth)

725
00:24:08,194 --> 00:24:10,364
(The married guy can relate to it.)

726
00:24:10,604 --> 00:24:11,703
All right.

727
00:24:11,704 --> 00:24:13,833
- Isn't this a scenic spot?
- Yes.

728
00:24:13,834 --> 00:24:15,174
- This is a cool place.
- Yes.

729
00:24:15,504 --> 00:24:17,774
- It's a beautiful place.
- It's beautiful year-round.

730
00:24:17,944 --> 00:24:20,973
It's chosen as 1 of the 100 beautiful forests in Korea.

731
00:24:20,974 --> 00:24:22,143
- It's indeed a beautiful forest.
- Yes.

732
00:24:22,144 --> 00:24:23,614
It's a therapeutic spot in Naju.

733
00:24:23,744 --> 00:24:25,613
It's called the Jeollanam-do Forest Resources Research Institute.

734
00:24:25,614 --> 00:24:26,894
- The Research Institute?
- Yes.

735
00:24:28,114 --> 00:24:30,283
(It includes the metasequoia tree trail...)

736
00:24:30,284 --> 00:24:32,364
(as well as a beautiful variety of blooming plants.)

737
00:24:32,784 --> 00:24:37,293
(It's giving off the fresh, dewy scent of nature.)

738
00:24:37,294 --> 00:24:39,393
- The trail itself here is...
- It's so pretty.

739
00:24:39,394 --> 00:24:40,763
This trail looks so exotic.

740
00:24:40,764 --> 00:24:43,444
The air is fresh. The trail looks beautiful. This is the best spot.

741
00:24:43,504 --> 00:24:44,703
You'll play a random game...

742
00:24:44,704 --> 00:24:46,673
for your allowance at this open metasequoia trail.

743
00:24:46,674 --> 00:24:48,604
- Metasequoia...
- It's called...

744
00:24:49,204 --> 00:24:50,574
Steal the Naju Pears.

745
00:24:51,044 --> 00:24:52,920
- Steal the Naju Pears?
- You want us to steal them?

746
00:24:52,944 --> 00:24:54,573
- Out in the open?
- No. I know what this is.

747
00:24:54,574 --> 00:24:56,373
