- Yes.

763
00:25:27,044 --> 00:25:28,813
- Right.
- So we can steal several?

764
00:25:28,814 --> 00:25:30,114
Of course, we should.

765
00:25:30,184 --> 00:25:31,384
We must be a big thief.

766
00:25:31,984 --> 00:25:34,883
Let me introduce you to the orchard owners.

767
00:25:34,884 --> 00:25:35,954
Really?

768
00:25:36,384 --> 00:25:38,553
I have a bad feeling about this. I bet they can run really fast.

769
00:25:38,554 --> 00:25:40,793
Orchard owners, please come on out.

770
00:25:40,794 --> 00:25:41,824
- What?
- Where are they?

771
00:25:42,094 --> 00:25:44,564
(A group of orchard owners runs out energetically.)

772
00:25:45,124 --> 00:25:46,263
- They're kids.
- They're kids.

773
00:25:46,264 --> 00:25:47,333
- Kids?
- What?

774
00:25:47,334 --> 00:25:48,334
- Gosh.
- Hello.

775
00:25:48,335 --> 00:25:49,415
- Hello.
- What's going on?

776
00:25:49,594 --> 00:25:50,803
(The orchard owner are small and cute.)

777
00:25:50,804 --> 00:25:52,063
- Hello.
- Hello.

778
00:25:52,064 --> 00:25:53,373
- What's going on?
- Hello.

779
00:25:53,374 --> 00:25:55,234
- What's going on? Okay.
- Hello.

780
00:25:55,934 --> 00:25:57,203
(The adorable orchard owner shakes his hand first.)

781
00:25:57,204 --> 00:25:58,804
All right. Nice to meet you.

782
00:25:59,004 --> 00:26:00,313
- Nice to meet you.
- They're kids.

783
00:26:00,314 --> 00:26:01,513
- Are you the orchard owners?
- Yes.

784
00:26:01,514 --> 00:26:02,643
- Yes.
- You are?

785
00:26:02,644 --> 00:26:04,243
- I think they're all runners.
- I see. Look at their shoes.

786
00:26:04,244 --> 00:26:05,283
- My gosh.
- They're wearing running shoes.

787
00:26:05,284 --> 00:26:07,083
- I see. They must be good.
- They're all runners.

788
00:26:07,084 --> 00:26:09,413
We have special guests joining us for our mission.

789
00:26:09,414 --> 00:26:11,500
They're from the track and field mecca in South Jeolla Province.

790
00:26:11,524 --> 00:26:14,354
They are track and field athletes from Naju Jungang Elementary School.

791
00:26:15,654 --> 00:26:17,093
- Welcome.
- Naju Jungang Elementary School.

792
00:26:17,094 --> 00:26:18,563
- Naju Jungang Elementary School.
- Naju Jungang Elementary School.

793
00:26:18,564 --> 00:26:19,804
Naju Jungang Elementary School.

794
00:26:20,194 --> 00:26:22,634
(The track and field mecca for elementary schools)

795
00:26:23,064 --> 00:26:25,033
(They've won awards at national competitions...)

796
00:26:25,034 --> 00:26:26,734
(as well as regional competitions.)

797
00:26:27,104 --> 00:26:29,603
(Track and field athletes from Naju Jungang Elementary School)

798
00:26:29,604 --> 00:26:31,173
My name is Kim Hwan Hee. I'm in sixth grade.

799
00:26:31,174 --> 00:26:32,844
- He's in 6th grade.
- He's in 6th grade.

800
00:26:33,144 --> 00:26:34,713
(Mimicking his pronunciation)

801
00:26:34,714 --> 00:26:36,390
I compete in the 800m race and do shot put.

802
00:26:36,414 --> 00:26:38,043
- Shot put?
- Really?

803
00:26:38,044 --> 00:26:39,044
(Impressed)

804
00:26:39,045 --> 00:26:40,153
(That's amazing.)

805
00:26:40,154 --> 00:26:42,284
I'm also in sixth grade, and I'm Kim Min Soo.

806
00:26:42,584 --> 00:26:44,824
He pronounced "sixth grade" correctly.

807
00:26:45,254 --> 00:26:46,853
I'm Park Tae Young in sixth grade.

808
00:26:46,854 --> 00:26:48,324
Tae Young? I bet he runs fast.

809
00:26:48,694 --> 00:26:50,263
I'm Yoo Yoon Seo in sixth grade.

810
00:26:50,264 --> 00:26:51,293
Yoon Seo.

811
00:26:51,294 --> 00:26:52,923
I'm Yoo So Myung in fifth grade.

812
00:26:52,924 --> 00:26:54,033
- You're in 5th grade?
- In 5th grade?

813
00:26:54,034 --> 00:26:55,034
Yoo So Myung.

814
00:26:55,035 --> 00:26:56,294
She's the youngest.

815
00:26:56,734 --> 00:26:58,634
I'm Kim Seung Hyun in sixth grade.

816
00:26:59,304 --> 00:27:00,333
For your information,

817
00:27:00,334 --> 00:27:02,534
