- How many seconds?

836
00:27:33,674 --> 00:27:35,303
- She can...
- One hundred meters?

837
00:27:35,304 --> 00:27:36,503
Around 14 seconds?

838
00:27:36,504 --> 00:27:38,664
- Is it 14.98 seconds?
- I'm a little faster than her.

839
00:27:38,874 --> 00:27:40,544
Hey, she's only in elementary school.

840
00:27:40,574 --> 00:27:41,643
My record was 18 seconds when I was in 6th grade.

841
00:27:41,644 --> 00:27:42,713
I've got this.

842
00:27:42,714 --> 00:27:44,584
- What's your record?
- I'm a little faster.

843
00:27:44,914 --> 00:27:46,884
Would anyone like...

844
00:27:47,154 --> 00:27:49,683
to try a practice race?

845
00:27:49,684 --> 00:27:51,554
- A quick one on this path?
- Yes.

846
00:27:51,954 --> 00:27:53,593
- What do you think?
- Our ace should compete.

847
00:27:53,594 --> 00:27:55,693
- To be honest...
- Isn't it too easy for an ace?

848
00:27:55,694 --> 00:27:57,324
- Wouldn't this be funny?
- What?

849
00:27:57,894 --> 00:27:59,194
(What?)

850
00:27:59,464 --> 00:28:01,763
What if the gap between the worse...

851
00:28:01,764 --> 00:28:03,293
