- You know that, right?

968
00:31:52,094 --> 00:31:53,623
It's your motto. Don't get greedy.

969
00:31:53,624 --> 00:31:54,693
Yes, just get one.

970
00:31:54,694 --> 00:31:55,964
Just aim for the middle.

971
00:31:56,394 --> 00:31:58,563
Joon, it's not about stealing a lot.

972
00:31:58,564 --> 00:31:59,903
What's important is stealing something.

973
00:31:59,904 --> 00:32:01,403
- You must take something.
- What's 7 times 8?

974
00:32:01,404 --> 00:32:03,174
- Joon, what's 7 times 8?
- It's 56.

975
00:32:03,434 --> 00:32:04,744
What's 15 plus 18?

976
00:32:05,044 --> 00:32:06,044
Isn't it 30...

977
00:32:06,045 --> 00:32:07,550
- It's 33.
- Just start. You can't do it.

978
00:32:07,574 --> 00:32:09,173
Let's start Steal the Naju Pears.

979
00:32:09,174 --> 00:32:11,984
First player, get ready.

980
00:32:13,414 --> 00:32:15,184
Students, please get ready.

981
00:32:16,284 --> 00:32:19,654
I'm nervous. This is nerve-racking.

982
00:32:20,624 --> 00:32:24,663
(Relaxed)

983
00:32:24,664 --> 00:32:26,364
Here we go. Get ready.

984
00:32:27,134 --> 00:32:28,363
Do it slowly, guys.

985
00:32:28,364 --> 00:32:29,364
(Steal the Naju Pears, Round 1)

986
00:32:29,365 --> 00:32:30,964
Start.

987
00:32:32,264 --> 00:32:34,533
- Two, three, four.
- He's actually fast.

988
00:32:34,534 --> 00:32:36,034
Go for the third box.

989
00:32:36,374 --> 00:32:38,103
(At a fast speed, )

990
00:32:38,104 --> 00:32:39,804
(he arrives at the third box.)

991
00:32:40,444 --> 00:32:42,004
(What's the question on the third box?)

992
00:32:43,074 --> 00:32:44,343
(Calculate the number of players in the following sports.)

993
00:32:44,344 --> 00:32:45,683
(His hands approach the lock as soon as he reads the question.)

994
00:32:45,684 --> 00:32:48,260
