2006
01:04:09,779 --> 01:04:11,038
It's all about luck then.

2007
01:04:11,039 --> 01:04:12,979
Isn't the beef bone soup inside the balloon?

2008
01:04:13,349 --> 01:04:15,148
- Let it open.
- Then I'll open my mouth.

2009
01:04:15,149 --> 01:04:16,348
(Thinking positively because they're hungry)

2010
01:04:16,349 --> 01:04:18,848
You succeed if you cut a string that isn’t connected...

2011
01:04:18,849 --> 01:04:20,948
to the water balloon, with a 1-in-4 chance.

2012
01:04:20,949 --> 01:04:23,688
Only one string is connected to the water balloon.

2013
01:04:23,689 --> 01:04:25,288
- Just 1 string? It's doable.
- That's 25 percent.

2014
01:04:25,289 --> 01:04:26,859
That's only 25 percent.

2015
01:04:27,059 --> 01:04:28,928
Do we keep going until it breaks?

2016
01:04:28,929 --> 01:04:32,498
Whenever you cut the string without breaking the balloon,

2017
01:04:32,499 --> 01:04:33,899
you get your allowance...

2018
01:04:34,729 --> 01:04:37,089
- Will we get 50 percent of that?
- You should multiply it.

2019
01:04:37,339 --> 01:04:38,808
- Multiply the amount.
- Multiply it.

2020
01:04:38,809 --> 01:04:39,938
Trip Where Fun Is...

2021
01:04:39,939 --> 01:04:41,068
Trip Where Fun is Multiplied.

2022
01:04:41,069 --> 01:04:43,938
You'll get double the amount of the allowance.

2023
01:04:43,939 --> 01:04:46,509
- Trip Where Fun is Multiplied.
- For the next one, it's triple.

2024
01:04:46,779 --> 01:04:48,519
For the next one, it's quadruple.

2025
01:04:49,149 --> 01:04:50,279
Don't burst the balloon.

2026
01:04:50,519 --> 01:04:51,749
This is a chance.

2027
01:04:52,019 --> 01:04:53,118
This is the moment.

2028
01:04:53,119 --> 01:04:54,719
- If you fail, - If we fail?

2029
01:04:54,989 --> 01:04:56,788
- the water balloon will burst.
- That's right.

2030
01:04:56,789 --> 01:04:59,328
You'll lose the entry fee...

2031
01:04:59,329 --> 01:05:01,389
and the double or triple allowance as well.

2032
01:05:01,629 --> 01:05:04,029
- That's right.
- You'll lose the entry fee.

2033
01:05:04,499 --> 01:05:05,629
Why don't we do this?

2034
01:05:05,829 --> 01:05:07,298
We have the highest chance at the start.

2035
01:05:07,299 --> 01:05:08,638
- That's right.
- Let's place 30 dollars.

2036
01:05:08,639 --> 01:05:11,068
- For the first one.
- They'll give us an upper limit.

2037
01:05:11,069 --> 01:05:13,008
- How much is the entry fee?
- They'll put an upper limit.

2038
01:05:13,009 --> 01:05:16,178
The entry fee for the first round is two dollars.

2039
01:05:16,179 --> 01:05:17,778
- Come on.
- What?

2040
01:05:17,779 --> 01:05:18,978
- What is this?
- Let's go.

2041
01:05:18,979 --> 01:05:20,878
- Seriously.
- Come.

2042
01:05:20,879 --> 01:05:22,278
- Let's go.
- We can't do this.

2043
01:05:22,279 --> 01:05:24,248
- We can't do this.
- Let's go.

2044
01:05:24,249 --> 01:05:25,448
Let's go to the next game.

2045
01:05:25,449 --> 01:05:27,388
It goes up in the next round.

2046
01:05:27,389 --> 01:05:28,619
This is just the first round.

2047
01:05:28,759 --> 01:05:31,688
There's one string that will make it burst.

2048
01:05:31,689 --> 01:05:32,728
That's right.

2049
01:05:32,729 --> 01:05:34,628
- Then if...
- You'll cut one string...

2050
01:05:34,629 --> 01:05:36,998
- in each of the three rounds.
- You'll replace it?

2051
01:05:36,999 --> 01:05:39,098
- Even if we do it...
- They'll replace the balloon.

2052
01:05:39,099 --> 01:05:40,868
Are there three balloons? What do you mean?

2053
01:05:40,869 --> 01:05:42,368
(They clearly didn't understand.)

2054
01:05:42,369 --> 01:05:44,138
- Even if we do it...
- They'll replace the balloon.

2055
01:05:44,139 --> 01:05:46,339
- Really?
- We just need DinDin to understand.

2056
01:05:46,609 --> 01:05:47,868
We just need DinDin to understand.

2057
01:05:47,869 --> 01:05:48,979
Even if we do it...

2058
01:05:49,509 --> 01:05:51,378
- You're underestimating us.
- Everyone except DinDin, come.

2059
01:05:51,379 --> 01:05:52,878
- Come on.
- Carry on with him.

2060
01:05:52,879 --> 01:05:55,279
- He'll explain it to you.
- Just carry on with just DinDin.

2061
01:05:55,579 --> 01:05:57,078
Let's go. We'll just...

2062
01:05:57,079 --> 01:05:59,948
- go somewhere that's our level.
- I'll convince them.

2063
01:05:59,949 --> 01:06:01,119
- Okay.
- Let's go.

2064
01:06:01,589 --> 01:06:04,019
Let's go. Where should we go?

2065
01:06:04,389 --> 01:06:06,388
(Creaking)

2066
01:06:06,389 --> 01:06:09,698
- Let's go.
- Yes. We're below standard.

2067
01:06:09,699 --> 01:06:11,458
- They just need him.
- Let's go.

2068
01:06:11,459 --> 01:06:13,068
Let's go. Go forward.

2069
01:06:13,069 --> 01:06:14,749
(The offended guys stage a protest march.)

2070
01:06:15,569 --> 01:06:16,799
Come here.

2071
01:06:16,969 --> 01:06:18,609
- What?
- This is how it goes.

2072
01:06:19,509 --> 01:06:22,379
When one genius joins a group of idiots,

2073
01:06:22,839 --> 01:06:24,839
that genius becomes the odd one out.

2074
01:06:25,549 --> 01:06:27,608
You should think carefully before acting.

2075
01:06:27,609 --> 01:06:28,778
- So...
- You might get hammered down.

2076
01:06:28,779 --> 01:06:31,888
If you think about it, we'll only lose two dollars,

2077
01:06:31,889 --> 01:06:34,018
since we'll be winning more.

2078
01:06:34,019 --> 01:06:35,888
Shall we begin Round One with five dollars?

2079
01:06:35,889 --> 01:06:37,458
- Five dollars for Round One.
- Let's do it.

2080
01:06:37,459 --> 01:06:39,788
- Let's do it.
- That's a fair amount.

2081
01:06:39,789 --> 01:06:42,029
Don't put on a big smile. They'll think we're satisfied.

2082
01:06:43,159 --> 01:06:45,268
- We'll go along just this once.
- Five dollars.

2083
01:06:45,269 --> 01:06:47,968
Let's play rock-paper-scissors to decide the person to stand there.

2084
01:06:47,969 --> 01:06:49,968
- Rock-paper-scissors.
- Rock-paper-scissors.

2085
01:06:49,969 --> 01:06:51,769
(DinDin and Lee Joon lost.)

2086
01:06:52,139 --> 01:06:53,668
- Rock-paper-scissors.
- What?

2087
01:06:53,669 --> 01:06:54,909
- It's you two.
- It's just us.

2088
01:06:54,939 --> 01:06:57,578
(Don't tell me...)

2089
01:06:57,579 --> 01:06:59,349
(Is it going to be me?)

2090
01:06:59,609 --> 01:07:00,809
Rock-paper-scissors!

2091
01:07:00,881 --> 01:07:02,257
(DinDin will sit in the water bomb seat.)

2092
01:07:02,281 --> 01:07:04,880
- This is so annoying!
- Yes!

2093
01:07:04,881 --> 01:07:07,750
- He'll become the odd one out!
- He'll be hammered down!

2094
01:07:07,751 --> 01:07:09,020
He'll be hammered down.

2095
01:07:09,021 --> 01:07:10,150
(DinDin, the odd one out, is lonely because he's smart.)

2096
01:07:10,151 --> 01:07:11,350
His front teeth...

2097
01:07:11,351 --> 01:07:12,620
His front teeth will be hammered down.

2098
01:07:12,621 --> 01:07:14,690
(Stay strong, you odd one out.)

2099
01:07:14,691 --> 01:07:16,090
This is annoying.

2100
01:07:16,091 --> 01:07:17,990
- Let's cut it first.
- Let's go.

2101
01:07:17,991 --> 01:07:19,761
- Okay.
- What?

2102
01:07:19,861 --> 01:07:21,077
- There are four strings.
- Yes.

2103
01:07:21,101 --> 01:07:22,300
Let's cut all the four strings at once.

2104
01:07:22,301 --> 01:07:24,930
- Like this?
- You're a genius.

2105
01:07:24,931 --> 01:07:26,777
- Let's cut them all at once.
- This is a variety show.

2106
01:07:26,801 --> 01:07:28,170
Let's decide the person to cut the four strings.

2107
01:07:28,171 --> 01:07:29,340
Rock-paper-scissors.

2108
01:07:29,341 --> 01:07:30,341
Scissors!

2109
01:07:30,342 --> 01:07:31,540
- Yes.
- You always win in such games.

2110
01:07:31,541 --> 01:07:32,710
I'm so happy.

2111
01:07:32,711 --> 01:07:34,381
(Jong Min gets to cut the string.)

2112
01:07:35,251 --> 01:07:36,651
- It's me.
- Goodness.

2113
01:07:37,511 --> 01:07:39,980
It's five dollars. Make sure to write that down.

2114
01:07:39,981 --> 01:07:40,981
- Okay.
- Okay.

2115
01:07:40,982 --> 01:07:42,021
Hey!

2116
01:07:42,451 --> 01:07:44,320
Jong Min is performing a sword dance.

2117
01:07:44,321 --> 01:07:45,621
(Executioner Jong Min appears.)

2118
01:07:46,021 --> 01:07:48,731
(DinDin is sentenced to the water-bomb punishment...)

2119
01:07:49,231 --> 01:07:50,690
(for the crime of being too smart.)

2120
01:07:50,691 --> 01:07:51,901
Everyone.

2121
01:07:52,661 --> 01:07:53,900
Don't touch the strings.

2122
01:07:53,901 --> 01:07:55,901
Just look and make your selection.

2123
01:07:56,001 --> 01:07:58,030
You should know this, Jong Min.

2124
01:07:58,031 --> 01:07:59,840
Seeing me get wet...

2125
01:07:59,841 --> 01:08:02,541
might make you feel better,

2126
01:08:03,011 --> 01:08:05,380
but we have to earn money to have lunch.

2127
01:08:05,381 --> 01:08:06,480
That's our priority.

2128
01:08:06,481 --> 01:08:07,610
How would I know which string is connected?

2129
01:08:07,611 --> 01:08:08,710
I'd cut that string if I knew.

2130
01:08:08,711 --> 01:08:11,080
Why don't you tell us which string since you're smart?

2131
01:08:11,081 --> 01:08:12,780
Can you see which one it is?

2132
01:08:12,781 --> 01:08:14,050
We should look at that.

2133
01:08:14,051 --> 01:08:16,720
The wind is blowing now, and the yellow string is swaying less.

2134
01:08:16,721 --> 01:08:18,460
- Since there's weight...
- No.

2135
01:08:18,461 --> 01:08:20,660
- I think it's this one.
- The red one is also swaying less.

2136
01:08:20,661 --> 01:08:22,630
It's swaying a lot suddenly.

2137
01:08:22,631 --> 01:08:24,930
From the way it's shaking, the yellow one is swaying less.

2138
01:08:24,931 --> 01:08:26,330
It would be because something is hanging on it.

2139
01:08:26,331 --> 01:08:27,700
- This one...
- That's scientific.

2140
01:08:27,701 --> 01:08:29,377
(The yellow string sways less since it's connected to the balloon.)

2141
01:08:29,401 --> 01:08:32,201
That would be the case if they just tied them here.

2142
01:08:32,341 --> 01:08:35,171
But if they pulled them tight, they'd be the same.

2143
01:08:35,571 --> 01:08:37,441
(They're tightly tied.)

2144
01:08:37,641 --> 01:08:39,681
In the end, it's about fate.

2145
01:08:40,581 --> 01:08:43,110
I'll just go with the one in the middle. The green one.

2146
01:08:43,111 --> 01:08:44,650
Five dollars is at stake.

2147
01:08:44,651 --> 01:08:45,920
- I'll just cut it right away.
- What will it be?

2148
01:08:45,921 --> 01:08:47,221
It's just Round One.

2149
01:08:47,921 --> 01:08:48,921
You can't take it back once you've touched it.

2150
01:08:48,922 --> 01:08:50,520
You have to go with it once you've touched it.

2151
01:08:50,521 --> 01:08:52,920
- The first attempt!
- I'll do it!

2152
01:08:52,921 --> 01:08:54,291
- Let's go!
- I'll cut it!

2153
01:08:55,631 --> 01:08:57,491
(Snipping)

2154
01:08:58,761 --> 01:08:59,800
Yes!

2155
01:08:59,801 --> 01:09:01,201
It's so scary!

2156
01:09:01,431 --> 01:09:03,371
I thought this was the balloon!

2157
01:09:03,671 --> 01:09:04,700
You succeeded.

2158
01:09:04,701 --> 01:09:05,870
- I cut the right one.
- We have ten dollars.

2159
01:09:05,871 --> 01:09:07,701
You know,

2160
01:09:08,641 --> 01:09:10,911
if our scheme is right,

2161
01:09:11,611 --> 01:09:13,741
- It's the blue one.
- this is doable.

2162
01:09:14,281 --> 01:09:16,810
Let's do it. Let's go for it as this is just the first round.

2163
01:09:16,811 --> 01:09:18,150
- Okay. Let's do it.
- Shall we keep going?

2164
01:09:18,151 --> 01:09:19,151
(They move straight on to Stage 2.)

2165
01:09:19,151 --> 01:09:20,151
Can we keep going?

2166
01:09:20,481 --> 01:09:21,481
Yes!

2167
01:09:21,751 --> 01:09:23,820
Red. Let's go with red!

2168
01:09:23,821 --> 01:09:25,590
- I have a good feeling about this!
- We're going to do it!

2169
01:09:25,591 --> 01:09:27,060
- Okay.
- It's 15 dollars.

2170
01:09:27,061 --> 01:09:28,390
We'll earn 10 dollars to have 45 dollars in total.

2171
01:09:28,391 --> 01:09:29,560
If we pass this, we'll have 45 dollars.

2172
01:09:29,561 --> 01:09:30,630
Hold on.

2173
01:09:30,631 --> 01:09:32,401
One, two...

2174
01:09:34,131 --> 01:09:35,571
Okay!

2175
01:09:35,771 --> 01:09:38,130
(They earned 15 dollars.)

2176
01:09:38,131 --> 01:09:39,340
But it's so scary.

2177
01:09:39,341 --> 01:09:41,841
- Nice.
- How much do we have?

2178
01:09:41,911 --> 01:09:44,271
We have 45.5 dollars.

2179
01:09:44,341 --> 01:09:45,610
What do we do? Should we stop here?

2180
01:09:45,611 --> 01:09:47,810
- Let's stop.
- Should we stop?

2181
01:09:47,811 --> 01:09:49,450
- We could check in the first game.
- Twenty dollars.

2182
01:09:49,451 --> 01:09:50,550
- No.
- Fifteen dollars.

2183
01:09:50,551 --> 01:09:52,750
Think carefully. We won ten dollars.

2184
01:09:52,751 --> 01:09:53,950
We have to stop here.

2185
01:09:53,951 --> 01:09:55,920
- There are two more rounds.
- There are more rounds?

2186
01:09:55,921 --> 01:09:57,420
- Let's stop here.
- Stop.

2187
01:09:57,421 --> 01:09:59,290
- Stop.
- We should stop here.

2188
01:09:59,291 --> 01:10:01,091
Jong Min. Let's do it.

2189
01:10:01,221 --> 01:10:02,260
- What?
- Let's do it one more time.

2190
01:10:02,261 --> 01:10:03,830
- We shouldn't continue!
- Jong Min.

2191
01:10:03,831 --> 01:10:05,277
It's not the last round. We have two more.

2192
01:10:05,301 --> 01:10:06,930
- Come here.
- That's not right.

2193
01:10:06,931 --> 01:10:08,671
We won't lose anything.

2194
01:10:08,771 --> 01:10:10,900
If we're right, we earn money.

2195
01:10:10,901 --> 01:10:12,500
If we're wrong, we relieve our stress.

2196
01:10:12,501 --> 01:10:14,370
- Right.
- It's a win-win for us.

2197
01:10:14,371 --> 01:10:16,240
- We have a 50-percent chance.
- That's right.

2198
01:10:16,241 --> 01:10:18,010
But we can make that 100 percent.

2199
01:10:18,011 --> 01:10:19,040
That's right!

2200
01:10:19,041 --> 01:10:20,710
- We should continue.
- What do you think?

2201
01:10:20,711 --> 01:10:21,711
We should continue.

2202
01:10:21,712 --> 01:10:23,550
- Of course. Let's do it.
- Let's do it.

2203
01:10:23,551 --> 01:10:24,581
We'll keep going!

2204
01:10:24,881 --> 01:10:28,081
(He's sent back under the water bomb by the collective mindlessness.)

2205
01:10:28,181 --> 01:10:29,991
We'll go with blue!

2206
01:10:31,451 --> 01:10:33,561
- Three!
- If we succeed, it'll be amazing.

2207
01:10:33,621 --> 01:10:36,160
We have to have lunch!

2208
01:10:36,161 --> 01:10:37,260
It's not a losing game.

2209
01:10:37,261 --> 01:10:38,460
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

2210
01:10:38,461 --> 01:10:40,160
Let's go, DinDin! Make it back alive!

2211
01:10:40,161 --> 01:10:42,400
We're here for you! Let's go. One, two, three!

2212
01:10:42,401 --> 01:10:44,571
Let's go!

2213
01:10:45,341 --> 01:10:48,001
(They succeed against extremely slim odds.)

2214
01:10:48,101 --> 01:10:49,611
(They earned 20 dollars.)

2215
01:10:49,671 --> 01:10:50,971
We told you.

2216
01:10:52,111 --> 01:10:54,080
Seriously? Was it the yellow one?

2217
01:10:54,081 --> 01:10:55,550
This is amazing. We beat those odds.

2218
01:10:55,551 --> 01:10:57,711
- Twenty dollars.
- Twenty dollars, since it's double.

2219
01:10:57,881 --> 01:10:59,080
(They give them the allowance.)

2220
01:10:59,081 --> 01:11:00,081
How much do we have?

2221
01:11:00,082 --> 01:11:01,621
They must be shocked.

2222
01:11:01,891 --> 01:11:03,190
- We have 50.5 dollars.
- We had 45 dollars.

2223
01:11:03,191 --> 01:11:04,221
If we have 50 dollars...

2224
01:11:04,491 --> 01:11:06,290
-That's ten dollars per person.
- We need to play more rounds.

2225
01:11:06,291 --> 01:11:07,620
We just need 20 dollars more.

2226
01:11:07,621 --> 01:11:08,690
- That's right.
- Just 20 dollars more.

2227
01:11:08,691 --> 01:11:09,830
- Let's go!
- Let's do this!

2228
01:11:09,831 --> 01:11:10,961
Let's get Round Two going.

2229
01:11:11,531 --> 01:11:14,631
(They set up for Round 2.)

2230
01:11:15,931 --> 01:11:18,801
- What is this?
- They're really mad.

2231
01:11:18,971 --> 01:11:20,241
This...

2232
01:11:20,371 --> 01:11:22,470
- This is amazing.
- They're very angry.

2233
01:11:22,471 --> 01:11:24,170
The rules remain the same, right?

2234
01:11:24,171 --> 01:11:25,710
- That's right.
- How much can we place?

2235
01:11:25,711 --> 01:11:27,587
- Let's put 50 dollars.
- The fee is 10 dollars.

2236
01:11:27,611 --> 01:11:29,180
- Ten dollars isn't bad.
- It's not bad.

2237
01:11:29,181 --> 01:11:30,310
We have 50 dollars now.

2238
01:11:30,311 --> 01:11:31,851
- We just need two more wins.
- Right.

2239
01:11:32,021 --> 01:11:33,651
Of course. We should place the bet.

2240
01:11:34,681 --> 01:11:35,721
Ten dollars.

2241
01:11:36,651 --> 01:11:38,190
- Let's play rock-paper-scissors.
- Okay.

2242
01:11:38,191 --> 01:11:39,191
This makes me nervous the most.

2243
01:11:39,192 --> 01:11:41,520
I rarely get this feeling,

2244
01:11:41,521 --> 01:11:43,241
but I have it today. I won't get wet today.

2245
01:11:44,391 --> 01:11:46,461
(Se Yoon will sit in the water bomb seat.)

2246
01:11:47,161 --> 01:11:48,400
- Okay. I believe in you.
- Let's do it.

2247
01:11:48,401 --> 01:11:49,530
- One, two...
- We'll cut it.

2248
01:11:49,531 --> 01:11:51,051
- Trust us.
- That won't be connected.

2249
01:11:51,431 --> 01:11:53,441
(They just need to avoid 1 out of the 4 strings.)

2250
01:11:53,541 --> 01:11:54,747
- Three.
- That won't be connected.

2251
01:11:54,771 --> 01:11:55,811
- Se Yoon!
- Hold on.

2252
01:11:56,011 --> 01:11:57,670
- Okay.
- There's no way it's connected.

2253
01:11:57,671 --> 01:11:59,041
- Okay.
- Okay!

2254
01:11:59,811 --> 01:12:01,741
It didn't work!

2255
01:12:02,281 --> 01:12:04,680
Okay. How much do we have?

2256
01:12:04,681 --> 01:12:05,880
- I have a good feeling.
- How much do we have?

2257
01:12:05,881 --> 01:12:07,521
- Sixty dollars.
- We have sixty dollars.

2258
01:12:07,721 --> 01:12:09,351
We should think carefully.

2259
01:12:10,091 --> 01:12:11,621
There's another round.

2260
01:12:11,691 --> 01:12:12,891
Let's continue!

2261
01:12:13,721 --> 01:12:15,120
(The irresistible thrill of earning allowance money)

2262
01:12:15,121 --> 01:12:16,961
- We should think carefully.
- Go and sit.

2263
01:12:17,991 --> 01:12:19,730
He got excited again. Hold him.

2264
01:12:19,731 --> 01:12:21,001
Of course. Let's do it.

2265
01:12:21,761 --> 01:12:24,631
- It's Silly Gumajeok.
- Why are you so vicious?

2266
01:12:24,871 --> 01:12:26,000
- Let's continue.
- It's worth trying.

2267
01:12:26,001 --> 01:12:27,900
- Just one more time.
- Let's do it.

2268
01:12:27,901 --> 01:12:29,310
We should continue. Let's go.

2269
01:12:29,311 --> 01:12:30,340
Just cut any string.

2270
01:12:30,341 --> 01:12:32,441
(The water bomb suddenly sways in the wind.)

2271
01:12:32,741 --> 01:12:34,580
- Why is it suddenly so windy?
- We'll cut it.

2272
01:12:34,581 --> 01:12:35,581
Let's do it.

2273
01:12:35,582 --> 01:12:37,180
- I really can't tell.
- We'll cut the green one!

2274
01:12:37,181 --> 01:12:38,510
- Cut the green one.
- It's cold.

2275
01:12:38,511 --> 01:12:40,320
- Cut the green one!
- I'll cut the green one!

2276
01:12:40,321 --> 01:12:42,521
- Cut it!
- One, two, three!

2277
01:12:44,721 --> 01:12:45,721
Three!

2278
01:12:45,821 --> 01:12:48,260
- Okay!
- I told you it wasn't green.

2279
01:12:48,261 --> 01:12:50,190
- Let's stop now.
- Let's stop.

2280
01:12:50,191 --> 01:12:51,430
- Let's stop.
- One more time!

2281
01:12:51,431 --> 01:12:53,200
- One more.
- No.

2282
01:12:53,201 --> 01:12:55,601
- We should do it.
- It's a 50-percent chance.

2283
01:12:55,831 --> 01:12:57,600
- Hey.
- It's a 50-percent chance.

2284
01:12:57,601 --> 01:12:59,800
- The blue one is connected.
- A 50-percent chance.

2285
01:12:59,801 --> 01:13:00,900
The blue one is connected.

2286
01:13:00,901 --> 01:13:02,310
- It's a 50-percent chance.
- Think carefully.

2287
01:13:02,311 --> 01:13:03,670
- If we think...
- We should consider the chances.

2288
01:13:03,671 --> 01:13:05,511
- about the odds, we should stop.
- We should.

2289
01:13:06,711 --> 01:13:08,040
But if we think about our stress levels...

2290
01:13:08,041 --> 01:13:09,641
- Of course. Let's do it.
- Let's do it.

2291
01:13:11,251 --> 01:13:12,951
Of course. I should get wet.

2292
01:13:14,721 --> 01:13:16,220
- We'll cut it.
- We'll cut it.

2293
01:13:16,221 --> 01:13:17,690
- We'll cut it.
- Hold on.

2294
01:13:17,691 --> 01:13:19,091
Of course. We must do it.

2295
01:13:19,291 --> 01:13:21,321
- Go ahead.
- One, two, three!

2296
01:13:28,361 --> 01:13:30,800
(He was hit by the water bomb.)

2297
01:13:30,801 --> 01:13:32,741
I'm sorry, but sit under it again.

2298
01:13:33,671 --> 01:13:35,200
You should have filled it with more water.

2299
01:13:35,201 --> 01:13:36,841
(Thank you for the big laugh and advice.)

2300
01:13:37,141 --> 01:13:38,170
(He sits under the water bomb again.)

2301
01:13:38,171 --> 01:13:39,240
I'll count to three.

2302
01:13:39,241 --> 01:13:40,411
One, two, three.

2303
01:13:43,181 --> 01:13:44,611
(He gets the refreshing penalty.)

2304
01:13:47,051 --> 01:13:48,450
(It's as if he entered the water.)

2305
01:13:48,451 --> 01:13:50,191
The wind blew the water that way.

2306
01:13:50,621 --> 01:13:51,691
(Laughing)

2307
01:13:52,061 --> 01:13:53,360
It's blowing the water.

2308
01:13:53,361 --> 01:13:55,220
We should have stopped.

2309
01:13:55,221 --> 01:13:57,207
- We should have stopped.
- We should have stopped.

2310
01:13:57,231 --> 01:13:58,591
- Joon...
- Hold on.

2311
01:13:58,831 --> 01:14:00,631
(Dripping)

2312
01:14:00,731 --> 01:14:02,070
We should have stopped.

2313
01:14:02,071 --> 01:14:03,630
We should have stopped.

2314
01:14:03,631 --> 01:14:05,070
How much do you have now?

2315
01:14:05,071 --> 01:14:06,970
- It's 40 dollars.
- It's 40 dollars now.

2316
01:14:06,971 --> 01:14:09,040
What are we going to do? We have to finish the last round.

2317
01:14:09,041 --> 01:14:10,811
Let's just cut two strings and stop there.

2318
01:14:11,341 --> 01:14:12,341
Let's stop after cutting two strings.

2319
01:14:12,342 --> 01:14:14,110
- How much is the entry fee?
- This makes things unclear.

2320
01:14:14,111 --> 01:14:16,011
In the last round,

2321
01:14:16,381 --> 01:14:17,680
- All in?
- Voluntary?

2322
01:14:17,681 --> 01:14:19,021
There are two strings.

2323
01:14:19,881 --> 01:14:21,620
So you either lose the money...

2324
01:14:21,621 --> 01:14:23,420
or make it double.

2325
01:14:23,421 --> 01:14:24,520
I think we should go all in.

2326
01:14:24,521 --> 01:14:26,090
- Pick the next person.
- Let's decide that.

2327
01:14:26,091 --> 01:14:27,721
Rock-paper-scissors.

2328
01:14:27,791 --> 01:14:29,331
Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors!

2329
01:14:29,791 --> 01:14:32,401
(Seon Ho will sit in the water bomb seat.)

2330
01:14:32,601 --> 01:14:33,907
- Let's do this, Director.
- Yes?

2331
01:14:33,931 --> 01:14:35,060
- When the balloon is lifted, - Yes?

2332
01:14:35,061 --> 01:14:37,470
We want it to droop down as it's too heavy.

2333
01:14:37,471 --> 01:14:39,271
- Okay.
- Please put in a lot of water.

2334
01:14:39,801 --> 01:14:41,600
Great. The balloon looks great.

2335
01:14:41,601 --> 01:14:42,870
Right. Here you are.

2336
01:14:42,871 --> 01:14:44,471
(The entry fee of 25.5 dollars is paid.)

2337
01:14:44,511 --> 01:14:46,480
- Okay.
- I'm scared!

2338
01:14:46,481 --> 01:14:48,010
- It's okay!
- Let me ask you this.

2339
01:14:48,011 --> 01:14:50,331
- All right. Close your eyes.
- Hold on tight. Here we go.

2340
01:14:51,251 --> 01:14:52,251
Don't duck down.

2341
01:14:52,252 --> 01:14:53,651
- Don't move.
- Don't duck down.

2342
01:14:53,851 --> 01:14:54,881
Go!

2343
01:14:55,621 --> 01:14:56,621
(What?)

2344
01:14:56,951 --> 01:14:59,091
(He cuts it consecutively.)

2345
01:14:59,121 --> 01:15:00,121
Go!

2346
01:15:00,122 --> 01:15:02,161
(It's a pass.)

2347
01:15:03,261 --> 01:15:04,291
Gosh!

2348
01:15:05,091 --> 01:15:06,961
(Seon Ho dodges it swiftly.)

2349
01:15:07,001 --> 01:15:08,500
Did we pass? What was that?

2350
01:15:08,501 --> 01:15:10,700
- Gosh!
- He cut that one first.

2351
01:15:10,701 --> 01:15:12,641
(Why did you dodge it?)

2352
01:15:13,071 --> 01:15:14,700
(We expected more from you, Seon Ho.)

2353
01:15:14,701 --> 01:15:16,340
- Were you going to cut both?
- The plan was to...

2354
01:15:16,341 --> 01:15:17,640
give up if it pops on the first try.

2355
01:15:17,641 --> 01:15:19,310
I was going to cut the other one if it didn't pop.

2356
01:15:19,311 --> 01:15:21,981
- Really?
- You made a bet of 25.5 dollars...

2357
01:15:22,311 --> 01:15:24,010
- and have won.
- Okay.

2358
01:15:24,011 --> 01:15:25,410
We did really well.

2359
01:15:25,411 --> 01:15:26,520
Here's 51 dollars.

2360
01:15:26,521 --> 01:15:27,621
(They earn 51 dollars.)

2361
01:15:27,721 --> 01:15:29,020
- You earned 51 dollars.
- How much do we have in total?

2362
01:15:29,021 --> 01:15:30,320
You had 15 dollars.

2363
01:15:30,321 --> 01:15:31,950
- We have 66 dollars.
- We have 66 dollars.

2364
01:15:31,951 --> 01:15:33,260
We did it.

2365
01:15:33,261 --> 01:15:34,920
Gosh, we should get some Naju beef bone soup.

2366
01:15:34,921 --> 01:15:36,507
- That's enough, right?
- We can afford it.

2367
01:15:36,531 --> 01:15:37,660
- Let's go.
- Shall we go?

2368
01:15:37,661 --> 01:15:39,430
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

2369
01:15:39,431 --> 01:15:40,961
Let's go!

2370
01:15:42,671 --> 01:15:43,871
A miracle has happened.

2371
01:15:44,131 --> 01:15:45,670
We can each get a bowl.

2372
01:15:45,671 --> 01:15:47,200
- Nice.
- We must!

2373
01:15:47,201 --> 01:15:48,341
This is amazing.

2374
01:15:48,441 --> 01:15:50,370
We started with 1.5 dollars. It's a miracle.

2375
01:15:50,371 --> 01:15:52,480
We have 66 dollars when we started with 1.5 dollars.

2376
01:15:52,481 --> 01:15:53,910
Gosh! This is a miracle.

2377
01:15:53,911 --> 01:15:56,711
Each region had its own specialty,

2378
01:15:56,811 --> 01:15:58,687
but there was never a time when all five of us got to enjoy it.

2379
01:15:58,711 --> 01:16:00,450
- Right.
- Didn't that never happen?

2380
01:16:00,451 --> 01:16:01,750
- We're quite...
- We made it happen today.

2381
01:16:01,751 --> 01:16:03,690
- strong with team games.
- Right.

2382
01:16:03,691 --> 01:16:05,661
Gosh, I feel great.

2383
01:16:05,861 --> 01:16:08,391
We'll probably go to the place with long lines.

2384
01:16:08,561 --> 01:16:10,390
- The place you've been to?
- Right. It was packed.

2385
01:16:10,391 --> 01:16:11,830
I'm curious about that place.

2386
01:16:11,831 --> 01:16:14,131
- It was really good.
- I hope we go there.

2387
01:16:14,461 --> 01:16:19,341
(The members enter the center of Naju.)

2388
01:16:22,511 --> 01:16:24,510
Gosh, they're all beef bone soup places.

2389
01:16:24,511 --> 01:16:25,840
- They're all beef bone soup places?
- They're all beef bone soup places.

2390
01:16:25,841 --> 01:16:28,180
- You're right.
- "Beef bone soup."

2391
01:16:28,181 --> 01:16:29,880
There it is! That was the place I went to!

2392
01:16:29,881 --> 01:16:31,810
- Where?
- Was it this street?

2393
01:16:31,811 --> 01:16:33,850
- I've always wanted to go there!
- Gosh.

2394
01:16:33,851 --> 01:16:35,480
- Hello.
- Hello.

2395
01:16:35,481 --> 01:16:37,250
- Welcome.
- It's a pleasure to be here.

2396
01:16:37,251 --> 01:16:39,361
(The large caldrons welcome the members.)

2397
01:16:40,161 --> 01:16:41,720
Naju beef bone soup...

2398
01:16:41,721 --> 01:16:43,390
originated from Naju in the Jeolla Province.

2399
01:16:43,391 --> 01:16:44,660
It's a beef bone soup made...

2400
01:16:44,661 --> 01:16:46,700
by boiling the beef to be clear and light.

2401
01:16:46,701 --> 01:16:48,861
(Naju's representative health food)

2402
01:16:49,031 --> 01:16:50,130
The origin of Naju beef bone soup...

2403
01:16:50,131 --> 01:16:51,377
starts at the latter period of the Joseon Dynasty.

2404
01:16:51,401 --> 01:16:54,601
Naju was the center of transportation and distribution.

2405
01:16:54,941 --> 01:16:57,310
That was why it was a place where many cow deals were made.

2406
01:16:57,311 --> 01:16:59,881
Beef dishes developed naturally because of this.

2407
01:16:59,981 --> 01:17:02,850
The other parts of the beef had to be used...

2408
01:17:02,851 --> 01:17:05,181
and this dish was developed to quickly sell these parts.

2409
01:17:05,311 --> 01:17:07,720
It was like a fast food dish at the marketplace.

2410
01:17:07,721 --> 01:17:09,697
- As it was efficient to make?
- It could be made quickly.

2411
01:17:09,721 --> 01:17:11,490
Food at marketplaces couldn't be boiled for a long time.

2412
01:17:11,491 --> 01:17:13,760
This was made quickly after cooking the beef several times.

2413
01:17:13,761 --> 01:17:15,291
A clean broth was used as well.

2414
01:17:16,261 --> 01:17:19,161
Dishes like seolleongtang are made mostly with bones.

2415
01:17:19,931 --> 01:17:21,560
The Naju beef bone soup is made mostly with the meat.

2416
01:17:21,561 --> 01:17:23,207
(Naju beef bone soup's broth is made with the meat.)

2417
01:17:23,231 --> 01:17:24,730
That is why seolleongtang has a white broth...

2418
01:17:24,731 --> 01:17:26,440
and Naju beef bone soup has a clear broth.

2419
01:17:26,441 --> 01:17:27,500
(Seolleongtang with white broth)

2420
01:17:27,501 --> 01:17:28,717
(Naju beef bone soup with clear broth)

2421
01:17:28,741 --> 01:17:31,441
(It's repeatedly poured over with the clear broth.)

2422
01:17:31,511 --> 01:17:33,641
(Large pieces of suyuk fill up the bowl...)

2423
01:17:33,681 --> 01:17:36,611
(and it's topped with just a few simple toppings.)

2424
01:17:37,051 --> 01:17:40,681
(Have a bowl of Naju beef bone soup.)

2425
01:17:40,921 --> 01:17:42,951
This was the place Jong Min was boasting about.

2426
01:17:42,991 --> 01:17:44,420
Was this the place you came to while being on our show?

2427
01:17:44,421 --> 01:17:45,421
- Yes.
- Really?

2428
01:17:45,421 --> 01:17:46,421
You sat by the wall, right?

2429
01:17:46,422 --> 01:17:48,220
- Right.
- I remember that photo.

2430
01:17:48,221 --> 01:17:49,901
He ate like the man in "Solitary Gourmet."

2431
01:17:50,261 --> 01:17:53,401
(Jong Min came alone like the Solitary Gourmet.)

2432
01:17:55,061 --> 01:17:56,071
(Groaning)

2433
01:17:56,271 --> 01:17:58,931
(He really enjoyed it.)

2434
01:17:59,571 --> 01:18:00,700
This place is amazing.

2435
01:18:00,701 --> 01:18:02,200
This place is amazing. I love this place.

2436
01:18:02,201 --> 01:18:04,471
- You're a regular.
- I'm a regular.

2437
01:18:04,811 --> 01:18:06,841
- How much do you have right now?
- One, two,

2438
01:18:07,111 --> 01:18:08,910
three, four, five.

2439
01:18:08,911 --> 01:18:10,581
We might get more if I ask.

2440
01:18:10,681 --> 01:18:11,681
(Laughing)

2441
01:18:11,781 --> 01:18:12,921
Six.

2442
01:18:13,181 --> 01:18:14,580
- Six and six.
- Right. Six and six.

2443
01:18:14,581 --> 01:18:15,791
We have 66 dollars.

2444
01:18:15,991 --> 01:18:17,620
We want to ask for a lot of broth as we have a regular.

2445
01:18:17,621 --> 01:18:19,021
Here's the menu.

2446
01:18:19,591 --> 01:18:20,591
What?

2447
01:18:20,592 --> 01:18:21,720
(Beef bone soup: 13 dollars, Suyuk beef bone soup: 15 dollars)

2448
01:18:21,721 --> 01:18:22,790
(Suyuk: 40 dollars, Bowl of rice: 1 dollar)

2449
01:18:22,791 --> 01:18:23,990
How much will it cost then?

2450
01:18:23,991 --> 01:18:26,301
We're left with a dollar if we order 5 bowls.

2451
01:18:27,201 --> 01:18:28,977
- We have just enough.
- We're only left with a dollar.

2452
01:18:29,001 --> 01:18:30,401
We can add a bowl of rice.

2453
01:18:30,571 --> 01:18:33,001
What about the suyuk beef bone soup?

2454
01:18:33,601 --> 01:18:35,341
- Be quiet.
- Right.

2455
01:18:36,371 --> 01:18:38,110
Think about the money we have.

2456
01:18:38,111 --> 01:18:39,951
How can we get that when we don't have enough?

2457
01:18:40,281 --> 01:18:41,940
- Let's be satisfied with this.
- Right.

2458
01:18:41,941 --> 01:18:43,110
- Come on.
- He's right.

2459
01:18:43,111 --> 01:18:44,710
Have we ever enjoyed...

2460
01:18:44,711 --> 01:18:46,750
- a region's specialty together?
- We can have it together.

2461
01:18:46,751 --> 01:18:47,880
Then let's decide on this.

2462
01:18:47,881 --> 01:18:49,820
Let's decide on who will get the extra bowl of rice...

2463
01:18:49,821 --> 01:18:51,121
by playing rock-paper-scissors.

2464
01:18:51,221 --> 01:18:52,251
Right. Let's do that.

2465
01:18:52,361 --> 01:18:54,360
- This is for the bowl of rice.
- Right.

2466
01:18:54,361 --> 01:18:56,081
- Ready...
- We won't get the suyuk, right?

2467
01:18:57,391 --> 01:18:59,961
- The suyuk here is amazing.
- Suyuk?

2468
01:19:00,461 --> 01:19:01,960
We're left with 26 dollars if we get the suyuk?

2469
01:19:01,961 --> 01:19:03,030
What will we do with that?

2470
01:19:03,031 --> 01:19:04,300
- That's two bowls.
- Two bowls?

2471
01:19:04,301 --> 01:19:06,671
- A plate of suyuk and... Right.
- That won't work.

2472
01:19:06,971 --> 01:19:08,600
I can't believe you're being like this...

2473
01:19:08,601 --> 01:19:09,610
after writing down 1.5 dollars.

2474
01:19:09,611 --> 01:19:10,710
(This is all because of you.)

2475
01:19:10,711 --> 01:19:12,611
- I just can't believe it.
- Right.

2476
01:19:12,711 --> 01:19:14,810
If he was my actual brother, I would've gotten really mad.

2477
01:19:14,811 --> 01:19:16,680
I would've said, "Think about our family circumstances!"

2478
01:19:16,681 --> 01:19:18,881
The best thing I did was to be born faster than DinDin.

2479
01:19:19,951 --> 01:19:21,597
It would've been terrible if we were younger than DinDin.

2480
01:19:21,621 --> 01:19:23,350
- He would've gnawed us down.
- Right.

2481
01:19:23,351 --> 01:19:24,950
- Gosh.
- You're in big trouble.

2482
01:19:24,951 --> 01:19:28,490
Five bowls of beef bone soup and a bowl of rice works perfectly.

2483
01:19:28,491 --> 01:19:29,771
- That works perfectly.
- Right.

2484
01:19:29,931 --> 01:19:30,960
This is for the bowl of rice.

2485
01:19:30,961 --> 01:19:33,400
Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors.

2486
01:19:33,401 --> 01:19:34,901
(He's the only one that played rock.)

2487
01:19:34,931 --> 01:19:36,730
Okay!

2488
01:19:36,731 --> 01:19:38,211
(DinDin wins the extra bowl of rice.)

2489
01:19:38,431 --> 01:19:39,641
He won't be able to finish it.

2490
01:19:39,701 --> 01:19:42,041
This is better for us. He won't be able to finish it.

2491
01:19:42,541 --> 01:19:45,411
All right. I will take your money.

2492
01:19:45,911 --> 01:19:47,680
If we had just one more dollar,

2493
01:19:47,681 --> 01:19:48,740
one person would've been able to have the suyuk beef bone soup.

2494
01:19:48,741 --> 01:19:49,810
Right.

2495
01:19:49,811 --> 01:19:51,557
(It's quite disappointing not to have the suyuk beef bone soup.)

2496
01:19:51,581 --> 01:19:53,081
- Then...
- An upgrade?

2497
01:19:53,251 --> 01:19:54,251
An upgrade for the regular?

2498
01:19:54,252 --> 01:19:56,191
I'm sure I can get an upgrade as a regular.

2499
01:19:56,421 --> 01:19:58,690
We'll decide on one winner through rock-paper-scissors.

2500
01:19:58,691 --> 01:19:59,821
- One?
- One?

2501
01:19:59,921 --> 01:20:00,961
Two?

2502
01:20:01,061 --> 01:20:02,361
- Two?
- Three!

2503
01:20:02,831 --> 01:20:04,291
It was really cold outside.

2504
01:20:04,461 --> 01:20:05,630
It's 4pm right now.

2505
01:20:05,631 --> 01:20:07,861
It's almost time for the elders to go to sleep.

2506
01:20:08,731 --> 01:20:09,970
Shall we decide on two winners?

2507
01:20:09,971 --> 01:20:11,670
- All right.
- There's a good chance to win.

2508
01:20:11,671 --> 01:20:13,277
- There's a good chance to win.
- That's good.

2509
01:20:13,301 --> 01:20:15,661
- Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors!
- Rock-paper-scissors!

2510
01:20:15,771 --> 01:20:17,370
- Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors!
- Paper!

2511
01:20:17,371 --> 01:20:19,587
(Seon Ho and Jong Min play paper while the others play rock.)

2512
01:20:19,611 --> 01:20:21,310
(Jong Min and Seon Ho win the suyuk beef bone soup.)

2513
01:20:21,311 --> 01:20:22,850
Hey, Seon Ho. I'll make an offer.

2514
01:20:22,851 --> 01:20:23,851
Let's hear it.

2515
01:20:23,852 --> 01:20:24,880
I'll give you my bowl of rice.

2516
01:20:24,881 --> 01:20:26,927
Give me the suyuk beef bone soup. How does that sound?

2517
01:20:26,951 --> 01:20:28,527
The suyuk beef bone soup gets served with one bowl of rice.

2518
01:20:28,551 --> 01:20:30,320
(Will it be the suyuk beef bone soup or the extra bowl of rice?)

2519
01:20:30,321 --> 01:20:31,401
Give me some time to think.

2520
01:20:31,521 --> 01:20:34,660
You'll get the beef bone soup with my bowl of rice.

2521
01:20:34,661 --> 01:20:37,230
- This is a very attractive offer.
- You'll only get one bowl of rice.

2522
01:20:37,231 --> 01:20:38,360
- Think carefully.
- You're thinking about this?

2523
01:20:38,361 --> 01:20:39,430
I would take that offer right away.

2524
01:20:39,431 --> 01:20:41,330
You only get one bowl of rice with the beef bone soup.

2525
01:20:41,331 --> 01:20:43,651
Will one bowl of rice be enough for you? I don't think so.

2526
01:20:44,131 --> 01:20:46,170
- Of course. We must do it.
- We must do it.

2527
01:20:46,171 --> 01:20:47,401
Okay!

2528
01:20:47,601 --> 01:20:49,071
I'll get the suyuk beef bone soup!

2529
01:20:49,611 --> 01:20:51,810
So there will be two bowls of suyuk beef bone soup.

2530
01:20:51,811 --> 01:20:53,817
Three bowls of beef bone soup and an extra bowl of rice.

2531
01:20:53,841 --> 01:20:55,080
- Here it comes!
- It's here!

2532
01:20:55,081 --> 01:20:56,211
Who ordered beef bone soup?

2533
01:20:57,711 --> 01:20:59,320
- I was here before.
- Right.

2534
01:20:59,321 --> 01:21:00,480
- He's a regular.
- Gosh. It's great to see you.

2535
01:21:00,481 --> 01:21:01,650
- I'm a regular.
- He's a regular.

2536
01:21:01,651 --> 01:21:04,690
Ma'am, Jong Min said we would be able to get some more...

2537
01:21:04,691 --> 01:21:06,920
if we mention his name.

2538
01:21:06,921 --> 01:21:09,561
- Is that true?
- Right. We must serve you more.

2539
01:21:09,931 --> 01:21:12,861
- Really?
- I thought Yunho was here.

2540
01:21:12,961 --> 01:21:14,130
"We must!"

2541
01:21:14,131 --> 01:21:17,331
Will you not serve us more under a different name?

2542
01:21:17,471 --> 01:21:18,871
- We'll serve you more.
- Gosh!

2543
01:21:19,301 --> 01:21:20,441
It's the same for anyone!

2544
01:21:21,241 --> 01:21:22,970
- Enjoy your meal.
- Thank you!

2545
01:21:22,971 --> 01:21:24,111
Thank you, ma'am!

2546
01:21:24,341 --> 01:21:26,811
- Gosh!
- It looks amazing.

2547
01:21:28,241 --> 01:21:29,311
Thank you for the food.

2548
01:21:30,081 --> 01:21:31,181
Enjoy your meal.

2549
01:21:31,451 --> 01:21:33,281
(He starts with the soup.)

2550
01:21:33,321 --> 01:21:34,480
Gosh, this is it!

2551
01:21:34,481 --> 01:21:37,051
(It still tastes great.)

2552
01:21:37,191 --> 01:21:39,020
(Se Yoon tries the soup.)

2553
01:21:39,021 --> 01:21:40,061
(Letting out a breath)

2554
01:21:40,161 --> 01:21:42,120
(Se Yoon tries the soup twice.)

2555
01:21:42,121 --> 01:21:43,191
(Letting out a breath)

2556
01:21:44,161 --> 01:21:46,060
(Se Yoon tries the soup 3 times.)

2557
01:21:46,061 --> 01:21:47,601
- Gosh!
- Gosh, it's so clear!

2558
01:21:49,571 --> 01:21:51,131
- Gosh!
- Gosh, it's so clear!

2559
01:21:51,471 --> 01:21:53,771
Gosh, it's so good!

2560
01:21:54,901 --> 01:21:56,821
- It's really good.
- Is the chili pepper spicy?

2561
01:21:57,471 --> 01:21:59,610
- It isn't spicy?
- The meat doesn't smell bad at all.

2562
01:21:59,611 --> 01:22:02,751
The soup is really clear and refreshing.

2563
01:22:03,681 --> 01:22:05,211
It's really clean. Gosh!

2564
01:22:06,181 --> 01:22:08,281
It would've been terrible to miss out on this.

2565
01:22:08,751 --> 01:22:10,690
It would've been terrible to miss out on this.

2566
01:22:10,691 --> 01:22:12,691
It would've been upsetting to miss out on this.

2567
01:22:13,191 --> 01:22:16,991
(Jong Min, the regular, is enjoying it once again.)

2568
01:22:17,861 --> 01:22:20,531
(Taking a big bite of the Naju beef bone soup)

2569
01:22:20,561 --> 01:22:21,600
(Satisfied)

2570
01:22:21,601 --> 01:22:23,281
- I should try it with the kimchi.
- Gosh.

2571
01:22:25,271 --> 01:22:27,001
The kimchi is the type that Se Yoon likes.

2572
01:22:27,101 --> 01:22:28,271
Se Yoon would love this.

2573
01:22:30,311 --> 01:22:31,311
Did you feel it?

2574
01:22:33,211 --> 01:22:38,551
(A touching combination that is hard to describe)

2575
01:22:39,151 --> 01:22:42,551
(A taste that calls for a second round right away)

2576
01:22:44,391 --> 01:22:45,961
(Greatly satisfied)

2577
01:22:46,291 --> 01:22:47,837
The aged kimchi was perfectly aged, wasn't it?

2578
01:22:47,861 --> 01:22:49,890
The kimchi is amazing.

2579
01:22:49,891 --> 01:22:50,990
The kimchi.

2580
01:22:50,991 --> 01:22:52,951
It makes you want to eat the whole piece at once.

2581
01:22:53,861 --> 01:22:55,501
(This is how it must be enjoyed.)

2582
01:22:56,171 --> 01:22:58,030
(Making a big sigh)

2583
01:22:58,031 --> 01:22:59,207
You know this feeling, don't you?

2584
01:22:59,231 --> 01:23:01,512
You get annoyed as you eat because the food gets smaller.

2585
01:23:02,371 --> 01:23:03,371
It's upsetting.

2586
01:23:03,372 --> 01:23:05,340
I think I would be fine with having this for breakfast and dinner.

2587
01:23:05,341 --> 01:23:06,841
- Right.
- That's how good it is.

2588
01:23:07,711 --> 01:23:09,380
Please get us a refill for the kimchi.

2589
01:23:09,381 --> 01:23:11,381
- A refill for the kimchi?
- I'll go.

2590
01:23:11,811 --> 01:23:13,080
Enough for each person.

2591
01:23:13,081 --> 01:23:15,362
- Bring around 2 to 3 plates.
- I'll bring 2 to 3 plates.

2592
01:23:23,131 --> 01:23:25,391
Gosh, I keep getting bad thoughts.

2593
01:23:27,361 --> 01:23:30,331
(Se Yoon feels tempted by this sight.)

2594
01:23:30,601 --> 01:23:32,371
Oh, come on.

2595
01:23:33,001 --> 01:23:34,721
The younger one went to get us more kimchi.

2596
01:23:35,141 --> 01:23:36,640
How can you covet after his food?

2597
01:23:36,641 --> 01:23:37,940
That's what you're thinking about?

2598
01:23:37,941 --> 01:23:40,181
I wish I could control myself from these thoughts.

2599
01:23:40,281 --> 01:23:41,617
I wish to be free from these thoughts.

2600
01:23:41,641 --> 01:23:43,050
After scooping that part,

2601
01:23:43,051 --> 01:23:44,880
it would be great to have a piece of kimchi.

2602
01:23:44,881 --> 01:23:46,980
- Take a bite of it.
- Take one bite.

2603
01:23:46,981 --> 01:23:48,780
- Take one bite.
- How can I when he's not here?

2604
01:23:48,781 --> 01:23:49,991
That's stealing.

2605
01:23:50,521 --> 01:23:51,521
I'll scoop it.

2606
01:23:53,161 --> 01:23:54,461
Like the balloon bread?

2607
01:23:54,721 --> 01:23:57,130
I'll scoop it out. Cover it up now.

2608
01:23:57,131 --> 01:23:58,760
- It's quite obvious.
- Cover it.

2609
01:23:58,761 --> 01:24:00,301
- It isn't.
- Try to fill in the gap.

2610
01:24:00,431 --> 01:24:02,671
The kimchi here is amazing.

2611
01:24:03,031 --> 01:24:05,070
I can have two bowls of rice just with the kimchi.

2612
01:24:05,071 --> 01:24:07,231
(After sending the youngest one to get more kimchi...)

2613
01:24:07,441 --> 01:24:08,471
Fill it up.

2614
01:24:08,971 --> 01:24:10,111
Gosh, that looks amazing.

2615
01:24:10,511 --> 01:24:12,410
- He won't know.
- It's Jeolla Province's kimchi.

2616
01:24:12,411 --> 01:24:15,181
- It must be eaten like this.
- There you go!

2617
01:24:15,381 --> 01:24:17,211
(The big thief)

2618
01:24:18,781 --> 01:24:20,021
You should take a bite as well.

2619
01:24:21,081 --> 01:24:22,081
(He starts making an accomplice.)

2620
01:24:22,082 --> 01:24:23,402
- He won't know.
- He won't know.

2621
01:24:23,621 --> 01:24:25,120
It must be filled.

2622
01:24:25,121 --> 01:24:26,220
(Seon Ho returns with a generous amount of kimchi.)

2623
01:24:26,221 --> 01:24:27,291
It must be filled well.

2624
01:24:27,791 --> 01:24:29,530
- You have to hurry.
- Hurry.

2625
01:24:29,531 --> 01:24:31,361
- He's coming.
- Fill it for me.

2626
01:24:31,561 --> 01:24:32,731
(He's here!)

2627
01:24:34,731 --> 01:24:36,271
Wait. What do we do?

2628
01:24:37,901 --> 01:24:39,801
- What are you doing?
- What?

2629
01:24:41,401 --> 01:24:42,401
What was that?

2630
01:24:42,402 --> 01:24:43,440
(The rice thief is caught red-handed.)

2631
01:24:43,441 --> 01:24:44,740
- Seon Ho is really surprised.
- It's not like that.

2632
01:24:44,741 --> 01:24:46,180
- What are you doing?
- I just...

2633
01:24:46,181 --> 01:24:47,410
(What is going on?)

2634
01:24:47,411 --> 01:24:49,510
- I...
- I was doing you a favor,

2635
01:24:49,511 --> 01:24:51,210
- but you stole my food?
- I know. Seriously...

2636
01:24:51,211 --> 01:24:52,881
- This is too much.
- Was it Joon?

2637
01:24:53,121 --> 01:24:55,050
You're unbelievable.

2638
01:24:55,051 --> 01:24:56,121
I just...

2639
01:24:56,491 --> 01:24:57,691
This is driving me crazy.

2640
01:24:58,921 --> 01:25:01,021
Joon, I didn't expect you to do that.

2641
01:25:01,291 --> 01:25:02,691
I didn't do it.

2642
01:25:03,831 --> 01:25:05,431
I was under coercion.

2643
01:25:05,661 --> 01:25:07,360
- Coercion?
- Yes.

2644
01:25:07,361 --> 01:25:08,801
I feel bad.

2645
01:25:09,471 --> 01:25:10,731
I'll eat it anyway.

2646
01:25:11,801 --> 01:25:14,041
- My goodness.
- I'm so jealous.

2647
01:25:14,441 --> 01:25:16,411
Seon Ho, this is yours.

2648
01:25:17,011 --> 01:25:18,271
Go ahead and eat it.

2649
01:25:26,121 --> 01:25:29,251
This alone is reason enough to come to Naju.

2650
01:25:29,921 --> 01:25:31,251
- That's true.
- Sure.

2651
01:25:31,551 --> 01:25:32,621
I like the expression.

2652
01:25:33,021 --> 01:25:34,021
Can I get more food then?

2653
01:25:35,691 --> 01:25:37,991
I say good things when I'm well fed.

2654
01:25:38,561 --> 01:25:40,761
We will go back to the base camp now.

2655
01:25:41,001 --> 01:25:42,900
They say there are...

2656
01:25:42,901 --> 01:25:44,631
a few places selling snacks on the way.

2657
01:25:45,031 --> 01:25:46,541
- We're out of money.
- Desserts?

2658
01:25:46,641 --> 01:25:48,300
They sell stuff...

2659
01:25:48,301 --> 01:25:50,071
like ice cream and twisted donuts.

2660
01:25:50,511 --> 01:25:51,511
We should eat.

2661
01:25:52,071 --> 01:25:55,010
But you've spent all your money.

2662
01:25:55,011 --> 01:25:56,041
That's the problem.

2663
01:25:56,111 --> 01:25:59,280
So, I'm thinking of drawing lots.

2664
01:25:59,281 --> 01:26:01,320
- Okay.
- Is it an individual game?

2665
01:26:01,321 --> 01:26:02,350
Here.

2666
01:26:02,351 --> 01:26:03,920
(Here comes the draw.)

2667
01:26:03,921 --> 01:26:05,221
Don't touch it yet.

2668
01:26:05,391 --> 01:26:08,920
There is only one winning ticket here.

2669
01:26:08,921 --> 01:26:10,391
- Gosh, that's tough.
- Here?

2670
01:26:10,431 --> 01:26:11,730
If you win,

2671
01:26:11,731 --> 01:26:13,760
you'll get to buy some snacks on the way.

2672
01:26:13,761 --> 01:26:15,060
- Okay.
- We will give you ten dollars.

2673
01:26:15,061 --> 01:26:16,631
Gosh, that's a lot.

2674
01:26:16,871 --> 01:26:18,500
I'll pick one.

2675
01:26:18,501 --> 01:26:19,541
Okay. Let's do that.

2676
01:26:21,241 --> 01:26:22,241
Go ahead, Se Yoon.

2677
01:26:22,242 --> 01:26:25,040
(Each member picks one ticket.)

2678
01:26:25,041 --> 01:26:27,740
It would be perfect to eat something sweet right now.

2679
01:26:27,741 --> 01:26:30,410
- I want to eat ice cream.
- I want a twisted donut.

2680
01:26:30,411 --> 01:26:31,451
I want ice cream.

2681
01:26:31,511 --> 01:26:33,351
One, two, three.

2682
01:26:33,421 --> 01:26:35,121
- Ta-da.
- Darn it.

2683
01:26:36,051 --> 01:26:38,420
(Win)

2684
01:26:38,421 --> 01:26:39,720
- This is unbelievable.
- Why?

2685
01:26:39,721 --> 01:26:40,761
Again?

2686
01:26:41,461 --> 01:26:43,361
(Shouting)

2687
01:26:43,731 --> 01:26:45,590
What's with him?

2688
01:26:45,591 --> 01:26:46,800
(Jong Min wins.)

2689
01:26:46,801 --> 01:26:47,860
(Feeling bitter)

2690
01:26:47,861 --> 01:26:49,301
He gets a heads-up or something?

2691
01:26:49,401 --> 01:26:50,701
What on earth is with him?

2692
01:26:50,971 --> 01:26:52,300
- This is amazing.
- Do you feel like...

2693
01:26:52,301 --> 01:26:53,600
someone is helping you?

2694
01:26:53,601 --> 01:26:55,840
- Yes.
- This doesn't make sense.

2695
01:26:55,841 --> 01:26:57,610
- How is this possible?
- I had no idea.

2696
01:26:57,611 --> 01:26:59,610
Diversity has disappeared, right?

2697
01:26:59,611 --> 01:27:01,541
We always have to watch Jong Min's reactions.

2698
01:27:01,911 --> 01:27:04,181
I know. He's always like this.

2699
01:27:04,281 --> 01:27:05,650
(Win)

2700
01:27:05,651 --> 01:27:08,580
People wouldn't even know when this was filmed.

2701
01:27:08,581 --> 01:27:10,420
- This week or...
- It's April now.

2702
01:27:10,421 --> 01:27:11,701
(The new reaction in April 2026)

2703
01:27:11,751 --> 01:27:14,360
Jong Min, why don't you pick one person to share the food with?

2704
01:27:14,361 --> 01:27:15,897
- That's good.
- You shuffle the tickets.

2705
01:27:15,921 --> 01:27:17,990
- The leftovers.
- After eating as much as you want,

2706
01:27:17,991 --> 01:27:19,160
you can share the leftovers.

2707
01:27:19,161 --> 01:27:20,660
But there might not be any food left.

2708
01:27:20,661 --> 01:27:22,000
- I don't know the prices yet.
- Right.

2709
01:27:22,001 --> 01:27:23,770
Someone to share with if there is any food left.

2710
01:27:23,771 --> 01:27:24,870
- In case there's any food left.
- Right.

2711
01:27:24,871 --> 01:27:26,240
I'll pick a person to share the food with.

2712
01:27:26,241 --> 01:27:27,640
- Just in case.
- Someone to finish the leftovers.

2713
01:27:27,641 --> 01:27:29,000
If it's delicious, I'll eat it all.

2714
01:27:29,001 --> 01:27:30,641
- Someone to finish the leftovers.
- Yes.

2715
01:27:30,671 --> 01:27:32,341
- Okay.
- Then, you hand out...

2716
01:27:32,641 --> 01:27:34,510
the tickets without looking at them.

2717
01:27:34,511 --> 01:27:36,227
- Okay.
- Even he doesn't know what's what.

2718
01:27:36,251 --> 01:27:37,711
I didn't look at them, seriously.

2719
01:27:38,711 --> 01:27:40,120
- I didn't look.
- Me neither.

2720
01:27:40,121 --> 01:27:42,580
(They take one ticket each once again.)

2721
01:27:42,581 --> 01:27:44,390
- You should open the remaining one.
- Okay.

2722
01:27:44,391 --> 01:27:45,920
If he wins again...

2723
01:27:45,921 --> 01:27:47,521
- Ready.
- I won't share the food, then.

2724
01:27:47,621 --> 01:27:49,421
Start.

2725
01:27:50,931 --> 01:27:52,590
(Win)

2726
01:27:52,591 --> 01:27:53,600
What?

2727
01:27:53,601 --> 01:27:55,100
- You knew it, didn't you?
- Darn it!

2728
01:27:55,101 --> 01:27:56,570
- No!
- What's this?

2729
01:27:56,571 --> 01:27:58,570
- I didn't look.
- You pulled a trick, right?

2730
01:27:58,571 --> 01:28:00,340
- I shuffled them.
- Come on!

2731
01:28:00,341 --> 01:28:01,601
I swear.

2732
01:28:01,771 --> 01:28:03,170
I saw him shuffle them.

2733
01:28:03,171 --> 01:28:05,111
- I kept shuffling them.
- He actually did.

2734
01:28:05,171 --> 01:28:06,211
I saw that.

2735
01:28:07,111 --> 01:28:09,181
(Let's see if it's true.)

2736
01:28:10,681 --> 01:28:14,021
(The draw started again.)

2737
01:28:14,651 --> 01:28:19,991
(He clearly shuffled the tickets.)

2738
